minator. 1/4 = 2/8 and 1/8 = 1/8. Since 2/8 > 1/8, 1/4 is larger than 1/8. When numerators are the same, the fraction with the smaller denominator is larger.','','2025-11-06 19:23:00.419000','2025-12-06 07:33:16.549000',3,15),(280,'What is the fraction shown in the image?','multiple_choice',1,1,'The image shows 5 parts out of 6 equal parts, which is 5/6.','questions/year3/fractions/image5.png','2025-11-06 19:23:00.534000','2025-12-06 07:33:21.490000',3,15),(281,'What fraction is represented in the picture?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Looking at the image, 5 parts out of 6 equal parts are shaded, which represents 5/6.','questions/year3/fractions/image5.png','2025-11-06 19:23:00.682000','2025-12-06 07:33:21.717000',3,15),(282,'What is the fraction of the shaded part in the image?','multiple_choice',1,1,'The image shows 1 shaded part out of 2 total parts, which is 1/2.','questions/year3/fractions/image1.png','2025-11-06 19:23:00.834000','2025-12-06 07:33:18.314000',3,15),(283,'What is the fraction of the coloured part in the image?','multiple_choice',1,1,'The image shows 5 coloured parts out of 6 total parts, which is 5/6.','questions/year3/fractions/image5.png','2025-11-06 19:23:01.360000','2025-12-06 07:33:22.119000',3,15),(284,'Evaluate: 4 + 5 × 2','multiple_choice',1,1,'Using BODMAS: Multiplication comes before addition. 5 × 2 = 10, then 4 + 10 = 14.','','2025-11-06 23:39:22.646000','2025-12-06 07:33:33.862000',5,16),(285,'Evaluate: 9 - 6 + 3','multiple_choice',1,1,'Using BODMAS: Addition and subtraction have the same precedence, so we work left to right. 9 - 6 = 3, then 3 + 3 = 6.','','2025-11-06 23:39:22.768000','2025-12-06 07:33:34.124000',5,16),(286,'Evaluate: 16 - 32 + 12','multiple_choice',1,1,'Using BODMAS: Addition and subtraction have the same precedence, so we work left to right. 16 - 32 = -16, then -16 + 12 = -4.','','2025-11-06 23:39:22.891000','2025-12-06 07:33:34.343000',5,16),(287,'Evaluate: 96 + (2 + 4 + 2)','multiple_choice',1,1,'Using BODMAS: Brackets come first. (2 + 4 + 2) = 8, then 96 + 8 = 104.','','2025-11-06 23:39:23.023000','2025-12-06 07:33:34.789000',5,16),(288,'Evaluate: 14 + √81 + 9','multiple_choice',1,1,'Using BODMAS: Square root comes before addition. √81 = 9, then 14 + 9 + 9 = 32.','','2025-11-06 23:39:23.145000','2025-12-06 07:33:34.964000',5,16),(289,'2568 + _____ = 3981','multiple_choice',1,1,'To find the missing number, subtract 2568 from 3981. 3981 - 2568 = 1413.','','2025-11-06 23:39:23.262000','2025-12-06 07:33:35.404000',5,16),(290,'1095 - _____ = 564','multiple_choice',1,1,'To find the missing number, subtract 564 from 1095. 1095 - 564 = 531.','','2025-11-06 23:39:23.378000','2025-12-06 07:33:35.916000',5,16),(291,'_____ × 15 = 405','multiple_choice',1,1,'To find the missing number, divide 405 by 15. 405 ÷ 15 = 27.','','2025-11-06 23:39:23.492000','2025-12-06 07:33:36.136000',5,16),(292,'_____ ÷ 16 = 102','multiple_choice',1,1,'To find the missing number, multiply 102 by 16. 102 × 16 = 1632.','','2025-11-06 23:39:23.626000','2025-12-06 07:33:36.304000',5,16),(293,'_____ - 852 = 1098','multiple_choice',1,1,'To find the missing number, add 852 to 1098. 1098 + 852 = 1950.','','2025-11-06 23:39:23.746000','2025-12-06 07:33:36.685000',5,16),(294,'I add 2, then multiply it by 5. The result is 40. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 40 ÷ 5 = 8, then 8 - 2 = 6. So the original number was 6.','','2025-11-06 23:39:23.870000','2025-12-06 07:33:36.896000',5,16),(295,'I multiply it by 7, then I subtract 12. The result is 9. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 9 + 12 = 21, then 21 ÷ 7 = 3. So the original number was 3.','','2025-11-06 23:39:23.981000','2025-12-06 07:33:37.604000',5,16),(296,'I add 11, then multiply it by 7. The result is 63. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 63 ÷ 7 = 9, then 9 - 11 = -2. So the original number was -2.','','2025-11-06 23:39:24.113000','2025-12-06 07:33:37.943000',5,16),(297,'I add 7, then double it. The result is 20. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 20 ÷ 2 = 10, then 10 - 7 = 3. So the original number was 3.','','2025-11-06 23:39:24.223000','2025-12-06 07:33:38.139000',5,16),(298,'I add 20, double it and subtract 25. The result is 75. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 75 + 25 = 100, then 100 ÷ 2 = 50, then 50 - 20 = 30. So the original number was 30.','','2025-11-06 23:39:24.337000','2025-12-06 07:33:38.343000',5,16),(299,'I think of a number. I multiply it by 4 and add 9. My answer is 7 times bigger than the number I started with. What number am I thinking of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the number be x. Then 4x + 9 = 7x. Solving: 9 = 7x - 4x, so 9 = 3x, therefore x = 3.','','2025-11-06 23:39:24.458000','2025-12-06 07:33:38.658000',5,16),(300,'I think of a number. If I multiply the number by 6 and subtract 4, I get the same answer as multiplying it by 3 and adding 14. What number am I thinking of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the number be x. Then 6x - 4 = 3x + 14. Solving: 6x - 3x = 14 + 4, so 3x = 18, therefore x = 6.','','2025-11-06 23:39:24.580000','2025-12-06 07:33:38.847000',5,16),(301,'Calculate: 4506 + 1347','multiple_choice',1,1,'Adding: 4506 + 1347 = 5853','','2025-11-06 23:39:24.695000','2025-12-06 07:33:39.032000',5,16),(302,'Calculate: 9875 - 4678','multiple_choice',1,1,'Subtracting: 9875 - 4678 = 5197','','2025-11-06 23:39:24.806000','2025-12-06 07:33:40.024000',5,16),(303,'Evaluate: 4² + 3³','multiple_choice',1,1,'4² = 16 and 3³ = 27. So 16 + 27 = 43','','2025-11-06 23:39:24.923000','2025-12-06 07:33:40.275000',5,16),(304,'Calculate: 456 ÷ 6','multiple_choice',1,1,'Dividing: 456 ÷ 6 = 76','','2025-11-06 23:39:25.049000','2025-12-06 07:33:40.562000',5,16),(305,'Calculate: 92 × 132','multiple_choice',1,1,'Multiplying: 92 × 132 = 12144','','2025-11-06 23:39:25.161000','2025-12-06 07:33:40.889000',5,16),(306,'Evaluate: √100 + 2²','multiple_choice',1,1,'√100 = 10 and 2² = 4. So 10 + 4 = 14','','2025-11-06 23:39:25.276000','2025-12-06 07:33:41.119000',5,16),(307,'Write down what BIDMAS/BODMAS stands for.','multiple_choice',1,1,'BIDMAS/BODMAS stands for: Brackets, Indices/Orders, Division, Multiplication, Addition, Subtraction. This is the order of operations in mathematics.','','2025-11-06 23:39:25.400000','2025-12-06 07:33:41.295000',5,16),(308,'Calculate: 9 + 2 × 5','multiple_choice',1,1,'Using BODMAS: Multiplication comes before addition. 2 × 5 = 10, then 9 + 10 = 19.','','2025-11-06 23:39:25.516000','2025-12-06 07:33:41.797000',5,16),(309,'Calculate: 12 ÷ √16 + 15','multiple_choice',1,1,'Using BODMAS: Square root comes first. √16 = 4, then 12 ÷ 4 = 3, then 3 + 15 = 18.','','2025-11-06 23:39:25.630000','2025-12-06 07:33:42.208000',5,16),(310,'Using the digits 4, 6 and 8 exactly once, as well as any operations, create a calculation to which the answer is 12.','multiple_choice',1,1,'One solution is 6 × 8 ÷ 4 = 48 ÷ 4 = 12. This uses all three digits (4, 6, 8) exactly once.','','2025-11-06 23:39:25.753000','2025-12-06 07:33:42.785000',5,16),(311,'Find the missing number: 1308 + _____ = 5667','multiple_choice',1,1,'To find the missing number, subtract 1308 from 5667. 5667 - 1308 = 4359.','','2025-11-06 23:39:25.869000','2025-12-06 07:33:42.985000',5,16),(312,'Find the missing number: 1452 - _____ = 657','multiple_choice',1,1,'To find the missing number, subtract 657 from 1452. 1452 - 657 = 795.','','2025-11-06 23:39:25.981000','2025-12-06 07:33:43.217000',5,16),(313,'I think of a number. I add 48 and then divide by 3. Finally, I square root my answer and the result is 9. What number am I thinking of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: If √(result) = 9, then result = 9² = 81. If (number + 48) ÷ 3 = 81, then number + 48 = 81 × 3 = 243. So number = 243 - 48 = 195.','','2025-11-06 23:39:26.116000','2025-12-06 07:33:43.383000',5,16),(314,'I think of a number. If I multiply the number by 7 and subtract 10, I get the same answer as if I multiply the number by 3 and subtract 2. What number am I thinking of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the number be x. Then 7x - 10 = 3x - 2. Solving: 7x - 3x = -2 + 10, so 4x = 8, therefore x = 2.','','2025-11-06 23:39:26.231000','2025-12-06 07:33:43.570000',5,16),(315,'I think of a number. If I multiply the number by 4 and subtract 2, I get the same answer as multiplying the number by 2 and adding 8. What number am I thinking of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the number be x. Then 4x - 2 = 2x + 8. Solving: 4x - 2x = 8 + 2, so 2x = 10, therefore x = 5.','','2025-11-06 23:39:26.350000','2025-12-06 07:33:43.856000',5,16),(335,'What is the volume of the spacecraft? (use π = 22/7)','short_answer',1,1,'Volume for the corn is 1/3πR²h and volume of cylinder is πR²h','questions/year6/measurements/image23.png','2025-11-07 23:13:26.040000','2025-11-09 10:39:05.782000',6,1),(336,'Find the circumference of this circle.','multiple_choice',1,1,'Radius = 15 cm, circumference = 2πr ≈ 2 × 3.14 × 15 = 94.2 cm ≈ 94 cm.','questions/year6/measurements/image10.png','2025-11-07 23:13:26.263000','2025-12-06 07:33:48.413000',6,1),(337,'Calculate the area of this shape.','short_answer',1,1,'Calculate the rectangle area and remove the triangle area. (area of triangle is 1/2 x base x height).','questions/year6/measurements/image22.png','2025-11-07 23:13:27.090000','2025-12-06 07:33:57.450000',6,1),(341,'Which coins make $1?','multiple_choice',1,1,'50c + 20c + 10c + 10c + 10c = 100c = $1. This combination adds up to exactly one dollar.','','2025-11-09 09:33:03.582000','2025-11-09 09:33:03.582000',3,17),(342,'How much money is this?\n\n$2 coin + $1 coin + 50c','multiple_choice',1,1,'$2.00 + $1.00 + $0.50 = $3.50. Add the values of all the coins together.','','2025-11-09 09:33:03.708000','2025-11-09 09:33:03.708000',3,17),(343,'You buy an ice cream for $3.50 and pay with a $5 note.\n\nHow much change do you get?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$5.00 - $3.50 = $1.