ng BODMAS: Square root comes first. √16 = 4, then 12 ÷ 4 = 3, then 3 + 15 = 18.','','2025-11-09 10:32:54.348000','2025-11-27 04:49:41.498000',6,16),(418,'Using the digits 4, 6 and 8 exactly once, as well as any operations, create a calculation to which the answer is 12.','multiple_choice',1,1,'One solution is 6 × 8 ÷ 4 = 48 ÷ 4 = 12. This uses all three digits (4, 6, 8) exactly once.','','2025-11-09 10:32:54.480000','2025-11-27 04:49:41.647000',6,16),(419,'I think of a number. I add 48 and then divide by 3. Finally, I square root my answer and the result is 9. What number am I thinking of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: If √(result) = 9, then result = 9² = 81. If (number + 48) ÷ 3 = 81, then number + 48 = 81 × 3 = 243. So number = 243 - 48 = 195.','','2025-11-09 10:32:54.605000','2025-11-27 04:49:41.799000',6,16),(420,'I think of a number. If I multiply the number by 7 and subtract 10, I get the same answer as if I multiply the number by 3 and subtract 2. What number am I thinking of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the number be x. Then 7x - 10 = 3x - 2. Solving: 7x - 3x = -2 + 10, so 4x = 8, therefore x = 2.','','2025-11-09 10:32:54.743000','2025-11-27 04:49:41.949000',6,16),(421,'I think of a number. If I multiply the number by 4 and subtract 2, I get the same answer as multiplying the number by 2 and adding 8. What number am I thinking of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the number be x. Then 4x - 2 = 2x + 8. Solving: 4x - 2x = 8 + 2, so 2x = 10, therefore x = 5.','','2025-11-09 10:32:54.870000','2025-11-27 04:49:42.115000',6,16),(422,'Which is longer and by how many millimetres: 1.24 m or 1458 mm?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Convert 1.24 m to mm: 1.24 × 1000 = 1240 mm. Compare: 1458 mm - 1240 mm = 218 mm. So 1458 mm is longer by 218 mm.','','2025-11-09 10:32:55.012000','2025-11-09 10:32:55.012000',7,1),(423,'Find the circumference of this circle.','multiple_choice',1,1,'Radius = 15 cm, circumference = 2πr ≈ 2 × 3.14 × 15 = 94.2 cm ≈ 94 cm.','questions/year6/measurements/image10.png','2025-11-09 10:32:55.133000','2025-12-06 07:01:28.173000',7,1),(424,'Which metric unit would be most appropriate for measuring the distance around the school?','multiple_choice',1,1,'The distance around a school perimeter is typically measured in kilometers.','','2025-11-09 10:32:56.013000','2025-11-09 10:32:56.014000',7,1),(425,'Which metric unit would be most appropriate for measuring the distance between two cities?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Distances between cities are measured in kilometers.','','2025-11-09 10:32:56.153000','2025-11-09 10:32:56.153000',7,1),(426,'I think of a number. I double it, add 15, and the result is 41. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 41 - 15 = 26, then 26 ÷ 2 = 13. So the original number was 13.','','2025-11-11 03:10:20.086000','2025-11-27 04:49:42.277000',6,16),(427,'I multiply a number by 5, then subtract 8. The result is 32. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 32 + 8 = 40, then 40 ÷ 5 = 8. So the original number was 8.','','2025-11-11 03:10:20.212000','2025-11-27 04:49:42.419000',6,16),(428,'I triple a number, then add 6. The result is the same as doubling the number and adding 14. What number am I thinking of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the number be x. Then 3x + 6 = 2x + 14. Solving gives x = 8.','','2025-11-11 03:10:20.326000','2025-11-27 04:49:42.564000',6,16),(429,'Evaluate: (5 + 3) × 4','multiple_choice',1,1,'Brackets first: (5 + 3) = 8, then 8 × 4 = 32.','','2025-11-11 03:10:20.445000','2025-11-27 04:49:42.711000',6,16),(430,'Calculate: 18 ÷ 3 × 2','multiple_choice',1,1,'Division and multiplication are done left to right. 18 ÷ 3 = 6, then 6 × 2 = 12.','','2025-11-11 03:10:20.554000','2025-11-27 04:49:42.844000',6,16),(431,'Evaluate: (12 - 4)² ÷ 8','multiple_choice',1,1,'Brackets first: (12 - 4) = 8. Then 8² = 64, and 64 ÷ 8 = 8.','','2025-11-11 03:10:20.667000','2025-11-27 04:49:42.990000',6,16),(432,'Evaluate: 5 × (9 - 3) + 2²','multiple_choice',1,1,'Brackets first: (9 - 3) = 6. Then 5 × 6 = 30, and 2² = 4. Finally 30 + 4 = 34.','','2025-11-11 03:10:20.789000','2025-11-27 04:49:43.146000',6,16),(433,'I think of a number. If I divide it by 4 and then add 7, the result is 12. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 12 - 7 = 5, then 5 × 4 = 20. So the number was 20.','','2025-11-11 03:10:20.911000','2025-11-27 04:49:43.309000',6,16),(434,'Calculate: 3 × (6 + 2) - 4²','multiple_choice',1,1,'Brackets first: (6 + 2) = 8. Then 3 × 8 = 24, and 4² = 16. Finally 24 - 16 = 8.','','2025-11-11 03:10:21.030000','2025-11-27 04:49:43.458000',6,16),(435,'Evaluate: 2³ + (10 - 4) × 2','multiple_choice',1,1,'Powers first: 2³ = 8. Brackets next: (10 - 4) = 6. Then 6 × 2 = 12. Finally 8 + 12 = 20.','','2025-11-11 03:10:21.163000','2025-11-27 04:49:43.597000',6,16),(436,'I think of a number. If I add 9, multiply by 2, and subtract 5, I get 31. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 31 + 5 = 36, then 36 ÷ 2 = 18, then 18 - 9 = 9. So the number was 9.','','2025-11-11 03:10:21.290000','2025-11-27 04:49:43.728000',6,16),(437,'Calculate: (3 + 5) × (2 + 6)','multiple_choice',1,1,'Brackets first: (3 + 5) = 8 and (2 + 6) = 8. Then 8 × 8 = 64.','','2025-11-11 03:10:21.412000','2025-11-27 04:49:43.862000',6,16),(438,'Evaluate: (9 - 3)² ÷ 9','multiple_choice',1,1,'Brackets first: (9 - 3) = 6. Then 6² = 36. Finally 36 ÷ 9 = 4.','','2025-11-11 03:10:21.525000','2025-11-27 04:49:44.000000',6,16),(439,'I think of a number. I multiply it by 5, then divide by 2, and finally subtract 10. The result is 15. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 15 + 10 = 25, then 25 × 2 = 50, then 50 ÷ 5 = 10.','','2025-11-11 03:10:21.652000','2025-11-27 04:49:44.143000',6,16),(440,'Evaluate: 10 + (6 × 3) - 4²','multiple_choice',1,1,'Brackets first: (6 × 3) = 18. Then powers: 4² = 16. Finally 10 + 18 - 16 = 12.','','2025-11-11 03:10:21.766000','2025-11-27 04:49:44.295000',6,16),(441,'You have two $2 coins and one 50c coin.\n\nHow much money do you have in total?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$2 + $2 + $0.50 = $4.50. Add the coins together.','','2025-11-11 03:17:03.095000','2025-11-11 03:17:03.095000',3,17),(442,'A sandwich costs $4. You pay with a $10 note.\n\nHow much change will you get?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$10 - $4 = $6. Subtract the price from the amount paid.','','2025-11-11 03:17:03.226000','2025-11-11 03:17:03.226000',3,17),(443,'Which of these is worth the most?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$5 is more than $2, $1, or 50c.','','2025-11-11 03:17:03.348000','2025-11-11 03:17:03.348000',3,17),(444,'You buy a toy for $6.50 and give the shopkeeper $10.\n\nWhat is your change?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$10.00 - $6.50 = $3.50.','','2025-11-11 03:17:03.460000','2025-11-11 03:17:03.460000',3,17),(445,'Which coins could you use to make $2?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$1 + $1 = $2 exactly.','','2025-11-11 03:17:03.566000','2025-11-11 03:17:03.566000',3,17),(446,'A pencil costs $1.50. You have $5.\n\nHow many pencils can you buy?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$1.50 × 3 = $4.50, which is less than $5. Four pencils would cost $6, too much.','','2025-11-11 03:17:03.681000','2025-11-11 03:17:03.681000',3,17),(447,'You have 4 coins: 20c, 50c, $1, and $2.\n\nHow much money do you have?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$2 + $1 + $0.50 + $0.20 = $3.70.','','2025-11-11 03:17:03.793000','2025-11-11 03:17:03.793000',3,17),(448,'A comic costs $4. You give $5.\n\nWhat coin could you get as change?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$5 - $4 = $1, so you get a $1 coin back.','','2025-11-11 03:17:03.904000','2025-11-11 03:17:03.904000',3,17),(449,'Which group of coins makes $1.50?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$1 + 50c = $1.50.','','2025-11-11 03:17:04.027000','2025-11-11 03:17:04.027000',3,17),(450,'You have $10. You spend $3 on lunch and $4 on a drink.\n\nHow much money do you have left?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$10 - $3 - $4 = $3.','','2025-11-11 03:17:04.135000','2025-11-11 03:17:04.135000',3,17),(451,'Liam buys a chocolate bar for $2.80 and a drink for $1.20.\n\nHow much does he spend in total?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$2.80 + $1.20 = $4.00.','','2025-11-11 03:17:04.256000','2025-11-11 03:17:04.256000',3,17),(452,'A sandwich costs $3.50 and a juice box costs $2.\n\nHow much do both items cost together?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$3.50 + $2.00 = $5.50.','','2025-11-11 03:17:04.379000','2025-11-11 03:17:04.379000',3,17),(453,'Emma has $10. She buys a toy for $6.75.\n\nHow much money does she have left?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$10.00 - $6.75 = $3.25.','','2025-11-11 03:17:04.496000','2025-11-11 03:17:04.496000',3,17),(454,'A packet of stickers costs $4.20. You pay with a $5 note.\n\nHow much change should you get?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$5.00 - $4.20 = $0.80 (80 cents).','','2025-11-11 03:17:04.616000','2025-11-11 03:17:04.616000',3,17),(455,'A muffin costs $2.40 and a smoothie costs $4.60.\n\nYou pay with a $10 note. How much change do you get?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$2.40 + $4.60 = $7.00. Then $10 - $7 = $3.00.','','2025-11-11 03:17:04.807000','2025-11-11 03:17:04.807000',3,17),(456,'You buy 3 apples that cost 60c each.\n\nHow much do you pay altogether?','multiple_choice',1,1,'60c × 3 = 180c = $1.80.','','2025-11-11 03:17:04.929000','2025-11-11 03:17:04.929000',3,17),(457,'A toy car costs $8.50. You have $10.\n\nDo you have enough money, and if yes, how much change will you get?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$10.00 - $8.50 = $1.50, so you have enough and get $1.50 change.','','2025-11-11 03:17:05.048000','2025-11-11 03:17:05.048000',3,17),(458,'Noah buys a comic for $3.80 and a pen for $1.20.\n\nHe pays with a $5 note. What is his change?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$3.80 + $1.20 = $5.00 exactly, so no change.','','2025-11-11 03:17:05.173000','2025-11-11 03:17:05.173000',3,17),(459,'A cupcake costs $2.25. You buy two.\n\nHow much do you spend?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$2.25 × 2 = $4.50.','','2025-11-11 03:17:05.285000','2025-11-11 03:17:05.285000',3,17),(460,'You buy a ball for $6. You have $10. Then you buy an ice block for $2.\n\nHow much money do you have left?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$6 + $2 = $8 spent. $10 - $8 = $2 left.','','2025-11-11 03:17:05.400000','2025-11-11 03:17:05.400000',3,17),(461,'You have two $1 coins and three 50c coins.\n\nHow much money do you have altogether?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$1 + $1 + 50c + 50c + 50c = $3.50.','','2025-11-11 03:17:05.509000','2025-11-11 03:17:05.509000',3,17),(462,'Which group of coins makes $2?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$1 + $1 = $2 exactly.','','2025-11-11 03:17:05.633000','2025-11-11 03:17:05.633000',3,17),(463,'You have a $5 note, a $2 coin, and a $1 coin.\n\nHow much do you have in total?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$5 + $2 + $1 = $8.','','2025-11-11 03:17:05.745000','2025-11-11 03:17:05.745000',3,17),(464,'Which coins could you use to make $1.20?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$1 + 20c = $1.20.','','2025-11-11 03:17:05.856000','2025-11-11 03:17:05.856000',3,17),(465,'You have 4 coins: 20c, 20c, 50c, and $1.\n\nHow much money is that?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$1 + 50c + 20c + 20c = $1.90.','','2025-11-11 03:17:05.970000','2025-11-11 03:17:05.970000',3,17),(466,'You buy a drink for $3.40 and pay with a $5 note.\n\nHow much change will you get?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$5.00 - $3.40 = $1.60.','','2025-11-11 03:17:06.088000','2025-11-11 03:17:06.088000',3,17),(467,'A book costs $8. You give the shopkeeper $10.\n\nWhat is your change?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$10 - $8 = $2.','','2025-11-11 03:17:06.219000','2025-11-11 03:17:06.220000',3,17),(468,'You have $10. You buy a toy for $6.75 and a drink for $2.25.\n\nHow much do you have left?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$6.75 + $2.25 = $9.00. $10 - $9 = $1 left.','','2025-11-11 03:17:06.348000','2025-11-11 03:17:06.348000',3,17),(469,'A sandwich costs $4.80. You pay with a $10 note.\n\nHow much change do you get?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$10.00 - $4.80 = $5.20.','','2025-11-11 03:17:06.470000','2025-11-11 03:17:06.470000',3,17),(470,'You buy a muffin for $2.50 and a cookie for $1.80.\n\nIf you pay with a $5 note, how much change will you get?','multiple_choice',1,1,'$2.50 + $1.80 = $4.30. $5 - $4.30 = $0.70.','','2025-11-11 03:17:06.589000','2025-11-11 03:17:06.589000',3,17),(471,'The width of a cube increases by 50%, but it remains a cube. What is the percentage increase in the surface area of the cube?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the original side length of the cube = x, Original surface area = 6𝑥². New side length = 1.5𝑥, New surface area = 6(1.5𝑥)² = 13.5𝑥². Percentage increase = (New surface area - Original surface area) / Original surface area * 100% = (13.5𝑥² - 6𝑥²) / 6𝑥² * 100% = 125%.','','2025-11-11 03:44:24.616000','2025-11-11 03:44:24.616000',6,1),(472,'The sides of a square are doubled. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the side = x, original area = x². New side = 2x, new area = (2x)² = 4x². Percentage increase = (4x² - x²) / x² × 100 = 300%.','','2025-11-11 03:44:24.750000','2025-11-11 03:44:24.750000',6,1),(473,'The radius of a circle increases by 20%. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². If radius increases by 20%, new radius = 1.2r. New area = (1.2r)² = 1.44r², meaning a 44% increase.','','2025-11-11 03:44:24.879000','2025-11-11 03:44:24.879000',6,1),(474,'The height of a cylinder is doubled and the radius is halved. What happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume = πr²h. New volume = π(½r)²(2h) = πr²h. The volume remains unchanged.','','2025-11-11 03:44:25.042000','2025-11-11 03:44:25.042000',6,1),(475,'The length of a rectangle is increased by 50%, and the width stays the same. What is the percentage increase in area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area = L × W. Increasing length by 50% makes it 1.5L, so new area = 1.5LW. Increase = 50%.','','2025-11-11 03:44:25.188000','2025-11-11 03:44:25.188000',6,1),(476,'A cube’s edge length is tripled. By what factor does its volume increase?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. If side is tripled, volume increases by 3³ = 27 times.','','2025-11-11 03:44:25.334000','2025-11-11 03:44:25.334000',6,1),(477,'All dimensions of a rectangular prism are reduced by 50%. What is the percentage decrease in its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ length × width × height. If each is halved, new volume = (0.5)³ = 0.125, meaning 12.5% remains, so an 87.5% decrease.','','2025-11-11 03:44:25.463000','2025-11-11 03:44:25.463000',6,1),(478,'The diameter of a circle is reduced by 40%. What is the percentage decrease in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². New radius = 0.6r, new area = 0.36r² → area decreases by 64%.','','2025-11-11 03:44:25.590000','2025-11-11 03:44:25.590000',6,1),(479,'The volume of a cube doubles. What is the percentage increase in the cube’s side length?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = ³√2 × old side ≈ 1.26×, which is a 26% increase.','','2025-11-11 03:44:25.715000','2025-11-11 03:44:25.715000',6,1),(480,'A rectangle’s perimeter is 60 cm. If both its length and width increase by 25%, what is the new perimeter?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Perimeter ∝ (L + W). If both increase by 25%, total perimeter increases by 25% → 60 × 1.25 = 75 cm.','','2025-11-11 03:44:25.841000','2025-11-11 03:44:25.841000',6,1),(481,'The surface area of a cube is 150 cm². If the edge length doubles, what is the new surface area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Surface area ∝ side². Doubling the side makes the area 4 times larger → 150 × 4 = 600 cm².','','2025-11-11 03:44:25.971000','2025-11-11 03:44:25.971000',6,1),(482,'A cube-shaped gift box has a side length of 10 cm. If the side is increased by 20%, what is the new volume of the box compared to the old one?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = 1.2× old side, so new volume = (1.2)³ = 1.728× the original.','','2025-11-11 03:44:26.100000','2025-11-11 03:44:26.100000',6,1),(483,'A rectangular water tank is 2 m long, 1.5 m wide, and 1 m high. If the height is doubled, how much more water can it hold?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles the capacity → 2× the amount of water.','','2025-11-11 03:44:26.226000','2025-11-11 03:44:26.226000',6,1),(484,'A cylindrical candle has a radius of 5 cm and height of 10 cm. If the radius is doubled and height stays the same, how many times greater is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cylinder = πr²h. Doubling radius makes r² → (2r)² = 4r² → volume increases 4 times.','','2025-11-11 03:44:26.359000','2025-11-11 03:44:26.359000',6,1),(485,'A cone has a radius of 3 cm and height of 8 cm. If both radius and height are doubled, how many times greater is the volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h. If both r and h double → (2r)²(2h) = 8× bigger.','','2025-11-11 03:44:26.499000','2025-11-11 03:44:26.499000',6,1),(486,'A cylindrical water bottle has a volume of 500 mL. If its height is doubled but the radius stays the same, what will the new volume be?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles volume → 500 mL × 2 = 1 L.','','2025-11-11 03:44:26.645000','2025-11-11 03:44:26.645000',6,1),(487,'A metal cube is melted and reshaped into a cylinder with the same volume. If the cube’s side is 6 cm, what is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cube = side³ = 6³ = 216 cm³.','','2025-11-11 03:44:26.795000','2025-11-11 03:44:26.795000',6,1),(488,'A cone and a cylinder have the same base radius and height. How does the volume of the cone compare to the cylinder?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h, while cylinder = πr²h. Therefore, cone = one-third of the cylinder.','','2025-11-11 03:44:26.939000','2025-11-11 03:44:26.939000',6,1),(489,'A cylindrical jar has a radius of 4 cm and height of 12 cm. If both radius and height increase by 25%, how many times larger is the new volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. New radius = 1.25r, new height = 1.25h → new volume = (1.25)³ = 1.953× larger.','','2025-11-11 03:44:27.068000','2025-11-11 03:44:27.068000',6,1),(490,'A swimming pool is shaped like a rectangular prism 8 m long, 4 m wide, and 2 m deep. If it is filled halfway, how much water is inside?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Full volume = 8×4×2 = 64 m³. Half full = 64 ÷ 2 = 32 m³.','','2025-11-11 03:44:27.195000','2025-11-11 03:44:27.195000',6,1),(491,'A cone-shaped paper cup has a height of 9 cm and radius of 3 cm. If both dimensions are halved, what happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. If r and h are halved → (½)³ = ⅛ → volume becomes one-eighth.','','2025-11-11 03:44:27.323000','2025-11-11 03:44:27.323000',6,1),(492,'Which fraction is equivalent to 1/2?','multiple_choice',1,1,'1/2 is equivalent to 2/4 because both represent the same value. When you multiply the numerator and denominator of 1/2 by 2, you get 2/4.','','2025-11-13 04:19:49.767000','2025-11-27 04:49:20.568000',4,15),(493,'Which fraction is equivalent to 1/3?','multiple_choice',1,1,'1/3 is equivalent to 2/6 because both represent the same value. When you multiply the numerator and denominator of 1/3 by 2, you get 2/6.','','2025-11-13 04:19:49.892000','2025-11-27 04:49:20.729000',4,15),(494,'Which fraction is equivalent to 2/4?','multiple_choice',1,1,'2/4 is equivalent to 1/2 because both represent the same value. When you divide the numerator and denominator of 2/4 by 2, you get 1/2.','','2025-11-13 04:19:50.013000','2025-11-27 04:49:20.902000',4,15),(495,'Which fraction is equivalent to 3/6?','multiple_choice',1,1,'3/6 is equivalent to 1/2 because both represent the same value. When you divide the numerator and denominator of 3/6 by 3, you get 1/2.','','2025-11-13 04:19:50.139000','2025-11-27 04:49:21.077000',4,15),(496,'Which fraction is equivalent to 2/8?','multiple_choice',1,1,'2/8 is equivalent to 1/4 because both represent the same value. When you divide the numerator and denominator of 2/8 by 2, you get 1/4.','','2025-11-13 04:19:50.281000','2025-11-27 04:49:21.247000',4,15),(497,'What is 1/4 + 1/4?','multiple_choice',1,1,'When adding fractions with the same denominator, add the numerators and keep the denominator the same. 1/4 + 1/4 = 2/4.','','2025-11-13 04:19:50.404000','2025-11-27 04:49:21.419000',4,15),(498,'What is 1/3 + 1/3?','multiple_choice',1,1,'When adding fractions with the same denominator, add the numerators and keep the denominator the same. 1/3 + 1/3 = 2/3.','','2025-11-13 04:19:50.536000','2025-11-27 04:49:21.577000',4,15),(499,'What is 1/5 + 2/5?','multiple_choice',1,1,'When adding fractions with the same denominator, add the numerators and keep the denominator the same. 1/5 + 2/5 = 3/5.','','2025-11-13 04:19:50.699000','2025-11-27 04:49:21.736000',4,15),(500,'What is 2/6 + 1/6?','multiple_choice',1,1,'When adding fractions with the same denominator, add the numerators and keep the denominator the same. 2/6 + 1/6 = 3/6.','','2025-11-13 04:19:50.838000','2025-11-27 04:49:21.898000',4,15),(501,'Which is larger: 3/4 or 1/2?','multiple_choice',1,1,'3/4 is larger than 1/2. To compare, convert 1/2 to 2/4. Since 3/4 > 2/4, 3/4 is larger.','','2025-11-13 04:19:50.965000','2025-11-27 04:49:22.055000',4,15),(502,'Which is larger: 2/3 or 1/2?','multiple_choice',1,1,'2/3 is larger than 1/2. To compare, convert to common denominator: 2/3 = 4/6 and 1/2 = 3/6. Since 4/6 > 3/6, 2/3 is larger.','','2025-11-13 04:19:51.098000','2025-11-27 04:49:22.215000',4,15),(503,'Which is larger: 1/4 or 1/3?','multiple_choice',1,1,'1/3 is larger than 1/4. When comparing fractions with the same numerator, the fraction with the smaller denominator is larger.','','2025-11-13 04:19:51.218000','2025-11-27 04:49:22.369000',4,15),(504,'Which is larger: 3/5 or 2/5?','multiple_choice',1,1,'3/5 is larger than 2/5. When fractions have the same denominator, the fraction with the larger numerator is larger.','','2025-11-13 04:19:51.345000','2025-11-27 04:49:22.516000',4,15),(505,'What is 1/2 of 8?','multiple_choice',1,1,'To find 1/2 of 8, divide 8 by 2. 8 ÷ 2 = 4.','','2025-11-13 04:19:51.466000','2025-11-27 04:49:22.651000',4,15),(506,'What is 1/3 of 9?','multiple_choice',1,1,'To find 1/3 of 9, divide 9 by 3. 9 ÷ 3 = 3.','','2025-11-13 04:19:51.585000','2025-11-27 04:49:22.780000',4,15),(507,'What is 1/4 of 12?','multiple_choice',1,1,'To find 1/4 of 12, divide 12 by 4. 12 ÷ 4 = 3.','','2025-11-13 04:19:51.717000','2025-11-27 04:49:22.920000',4,15),(508,'What is 2/3 of 6?','multiple_choice',1,1,'To find 2/3 of 6, first find 1/3 of 6 (which is 2), then multiply by 2. 2 × 2 = 4.','','2025-11-13 04:19:51.841000','2025-11-27 04:49:23.058000',4,15),(509,'What is 1 1/2 as an improper fraction?','multiple_choice',1,1,'To convert 1 1/2 to an improper fraction, multiply the whole number (1) by the denominator (2) and add the numerator (1): (1 × 2) + 1 = 3. So 1 1/2 = 3/2.','','2025-11-13 04:19:51.968000','2025-11-27 04:49:23.202000',4,15),(510,'What is 2 1/3 as an improper fraction?','multiple_choice',1,1,'To convert 2 1/3 to an improper fraction, multiply the whole number (2) by the denominator (3) and add the numerator (1): (2 × 3) + 1 = 7. So 2 1/3 = 7/3.','','2025-11-13 04:19:52.096000','2025-11-27 04:49:23.364000',4,15),(511,'Sarah ate 1/4 of a pizza. Tom ate 1/4 of the same pizza. How much pizza did they eat together?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Sarah ate 1/4 and Tom ate 1/4. Together: 1/4 + 1/4 = 2/4 = 1/2.','','2025-11-13 04:19:52.230000','2025-11-27 04:49:23.529000',4,15),(512,'A cake is cut into 8 equal pieces. John eats 3 pieces. What fraction of the cake did John eat?','multiple_choice',1,1,'The cake is divided into 8 equal pieces, and John ate 3 pieces. So John ate 3/8 of the cake.','','2025-11-13 04:19:52.356000','2025-11-27 04:49:23.697000',4,15),(513,'3/4 of a number is 15. What is the whole number?','multiple_choice',1,1,'If 3/4 = 15, divide 15 by 3 to find 1/4 = 5. Then multiply 5 × 4 = 20.','','2025-11-13 04:24:41.119000','2025-11-27 04:49:23.857000',4,15),(514,'2/5 of a number is 18. What is the whole number?','multiple_choice',1,1,'If 2/5 = 18, divide 18 by 2 to find 1/5 = 9. Then multiply 9 × 5 = 45.','','2025-11-13 04:24:41.259000','2025-11-27 04:49:24.008000',4,15),(515,'5/8 of a number is 40. What is the whole number?','multiple_choice',1,1,'If 5/8 = 40, divide 40 by 5 to find 1/8 = 8. Then multiply 8 × 8 = 64.','','2025-11-13 04:24:41.387000','2025-11-27 04:49:24.163000',4,15),(516,'3/10 of a number is 12. What is the whole number?','multiple_choice',1,1,'If 3/10 = 12, divide 12 by 3 to find 1/10 = 4. Then multiply 4 × 10 = 40.','','2025-11-13 04:24:41.512000','2025-11-27 04:49:24.300000',4,15),(517,'7/9 of a number is 35. What is the whole number?','multiple_choice',1,1,'If 7/9 = 35, divide 35 by 7 to find 1/9 = 5. Then multiply 5 × 9 = 45.','','2025-11-13 04:24:41.640000','2025-11-27 04:49:24.440000',4,15),(518,'1/3 of the apples in a basket are green. There are 12 green apples. How many apples are there in total?','multiple_choice',1,1,'If 1/3 = 12, multiply 12 × 3 = 36 apples in total.','','2025-11-13 04:24:41.793000','2025-11-27 04:49:24.586000',4,15),(519,'2/7 of the students in a class are left-handed. If there are 8 left-handed students, how many students are in the class?','multiple_choice',1,1,'If 2/7 = 8, divide 8 by 2 to find 1/7 = 4. Then multiply 4 × 7 = 28.','','2025-11-13 04:24:41.923000','2025-11-27 04:49:24.732000',4,15),(520,'5/6 of a ribbon measures 25 cm. What is the full length of the ribbon?','multiple_choice',1,1,'If 5/6 = 25, divide 25 by 5 to find 1/6 = 5. Then multiply 5 × 6 = 30 cm.','','2025-11-13 04:24:42.051000','2025-11-27 04:49:24.879000',4,15),(521,'3/5 of a tank is filled with 24 litres of water. What is the capacity of the tank?','multiple_choice',1,1,'If 3/5 = 24, divide 24 by 3 to find 1/5 = 8. Then multiply 8 × 5 = 40 litres.','','2025-11-13 04:24:42.179000','2025-11-27 04:49:25.029000',4,15),(522,'4/9 of a cake was eaten, which is 12 slices. How many slices were there in the whole cake?','multiple_choice',1,1,'If 4/9 = 12, divide 12 by 4 to find 1/9 = 3. Then multiply 3 × 9 = 27 slices.','','2025-11-13 04:24:42.304000','2025-11-27 04:49:25.180000',4,15),(523,'2/3 of a number is 14. What is 1/3?','multiple_choice',1,1,'If 2/3 = 14, divide 14 by 2 to find 1/3 = 7.','','2025-11-13 04:24:42.437000','2025-11-27 04:49:25.324000',4,15),(524,'5/6 of a number is 20. What is 1/2 of that number?','multiple_choice',1,1,'If 5/6 = 20, divide 20 by 5 to find 1/6 = 4. The whole = 24. Half of 24 = 12.','','2025-11-13 04:24:42.574000','2025-11-27 04:49:25.467000',4,15),(525,'3/8 of a number is 24. What is the number?','multiple_choice',1,1,'If 3/8 = 24, divide 24 by 3 to find 1/8 = 8. Then multiply 8 × 8 = 64.','','2025-11-13 04:24:42.697000','2025-11-27 04:49:25.604000',4,15),(526,'1/4 of a number is 9. What is 3/4?','multiple_choice',1,1,'If 1/4 = 9, then 3/4 = 9 × 3 = 27.','','2025-11-13 04:24:42.833000','2025-11-27 04:49:25.744000',4,15),(527,'2/5 of a number is 10. What is 4/5?','multiple_choice',1,1,'If 2/5 = 10, divide 10 by 2 to find 1/5 = 5. Then 4/5 = 5 × 4 = 20.','','2025-11-13 04:24:42.981000','2025-11-27 04:49:25.882000',4,15),(528,'I add 2, then multiply it by 5. The result is 40. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 40 ÷ 5 = 8, then 8 - 2 = 6. So the original number was 6.','','2025-11-15 08:50:50.226000','2026-02-14 00:02:10.442000',7,16),(529,'I multiply it by 7, then I subtract 12. The result is 9. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 9 + 12 = 21, then 21 ÷ 7 = 3. So the original number was 3.','','2025-11-15 08:50:50.335000','2026-02-14 00:02:10.588000',7,16),(530,'I add 11, then multiply it by 7. The result is 63. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 63 ÷ 7 = 9, then 9 - 11 = -2. So the original number was -2.','','2025-11-15 08:50:50.460000','2026-02-14 00:02:10.725000',7,16),(531,'I add 7, then double it. The result is 20. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 20 ÷ 2 = 10, then 10 - 7 = 3. So the original number was 3.','','2025-11-15 08:50:50.597000','2026-02-14 00:02:10.867000',7,16),(532,'I add 20, double it and subtract 25. The result is 75. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 75 + 25 = 100, then 100 ÷ 2 = 50, then 50 - 20 = 30. So the original number was 30.','','2025-11-15 08:50:50.698000','2026-02-14 00:02:11.001000',7,16),(533,'I think of a number. I multiply it by 4 and add 9. My answer is 7 times bigger than the number I started with. What number am I thinking of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the number be x. Then 4x + 9 = 7x. Solving: 9 = 7x - 4x, so 9 = 3x, therefore x = 3.','','2025-11-15 08:50:50.807000','2026-02-14 00:02:11.150000',7,16),(534,'I think of a number. If I multiply the number by 6 and subtract 4, I get the same answer as multiplying it by 3 and adding 14. What number am I thinking of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the number be x. Then 6x - 4 = 3x + 14. Solving: 6x - 3x = 14 + 4, so 3x = 18, therefore x = 6.','','2025-11-15 08:50:50.911000','2026-02-14 00:02:11.306000',7,16),(535,'Evaluate: 4² + 3³','multiple_choice',1,1,'4² = 16 and 3³ = 27. So 16 + 27 = 43','','2025-11-15 08:50:51.019000','2026-02-14 00:02:11.454000',7,16),(536,'Calculate: 456 ÷ 6','multiple_choice',1,1,'Dividing: 456 ÷ 6 = 76','','2025-11-15 08:50:51.130000','2026-02-14 00:02:11.617000',7,16),(537,'Evaluate: √100 + 2²','multiple_choice',1,1,'√100 = 10 and 2² = 4. So 10 + 4 = 14','','2025-11-15 08:50:51.234000','2026-02-14 00:02:11.762000',7,16),(538,'Write down what BIDMAS/BODMAS stands for.','multiple_choice',1,1,'BIDMAS/BODMAS stands for: Brackets, Indices/Orders, Division, Multiplication, Addition, Subtraction. This is the order of operations in mathematics.','','2025-11-15 08:50:51.346000','2026-02-14 00:02:11.894000',7,16),(539,'Calculate: 9 + 2 × 5','multiple_choice',1,1,'Using BODMAS: Multiplication comes before addition. 2 × 5 = 10, then 9 + 10 = 19.','','2025-11-15 08:50:51.447000','2026-02-14 00:02:12.036000',7,16),(540,'Calculate: 12 ÷ √16 + 15','multiple_choice',1,1,'Using BODMAS: Square root comes first. √16 = 4, then 12 ÷ 4 = 3, then 3 + 15 = 18.','','2025-11-15 08:50:51.555000','2026-02-14 00:02:12.178000',7,16),(541,'Using the digits 4, 6 and 8 exactly once, as well as any operations, create a calculation to which the answer is 12.','multiple_choice',1,1,'One solution is 6 × 8 ÷ 4 = 48 ÷ 4 = 12. This uses all three digits (4, 6, 8) exactly once.','','2025-11-15 08:50:51.662000','2026-02-14 00:02:12.327000',7,16),(542,'I think of a number. I add 48 and then divide by 3. Finally, I square root my answer and the result is 9. What number am I thinking of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: If √(result) = 9, then result = 9² = 81. If (number + 48) ÷ 3 = 81, then number + 48 = 81 × 3 = 243. So number = 243 - 48 = 195.','','2025-11-15 08:50:51.770000','2026-02-14 00:02:12.472000',7,16),(543,'I think of a number. If I multiply the number by 7 and subtract 10, I get the same answer as if I multiply the number by 3 and subtract 2. What number am I thinking of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the number be x. Then 7x - 10 = 3x - 2. Solving: 7x - 3x = -2 + 10, so 4x = 8, therefore x = 2.','','2025-11-15 08:50:51.894000','2026-02-14 00:02:12.611000',7,16),(544,'I think of a number. If I multiply the number by 4 and subtract 2, I get the same answer as multiplying the number by 2 and adding 8. What number am I thinking of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the number be x. Then 4x - 2 = 2x + 8. Solving: 4x - 2x = 8 + 2, so 2x = 10, therefore x = 5.','','2025-11-15 08:50:52.014000','2026-02-14 00:02:12.770000',7,16),(545,'I think of a number. I double it, add 15, and the result is 41. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 41 - 15 = 26, then 26 ÷ 2 = 13. So the original number was 13.','','2025-11-15 08:50:52.124000','2026-02-14 00:02:12.928000',7,16),(546,'I multiply a number by 5, then subtract 8. The result is 32. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 32 + 8 = 40, then 40 ÷ 5 = 8. So the original number was 8.','','2025-11-15 08:50:52.242000','2026-02-14 00:02:13.071000',7,16),(547,'I triple a number, then add 6. The result is the same as doubling the number and adding 14. What number am I thinking of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the number be x. Then 3x + 6 = 2x + 14. Solving gives x = 8.','','2025-11-15 08:50:52.344000','2026-02-14 00:02:13.212000',7,16),(548,'Evaluate: (5 + 3) × 4','multiple_choice',1,1,'Brackets first: (5 + 3) = 8, then 8 × 4 = 32.','','2025-11-15 08:50:52.442000','2026-02-14 00:02:13.349000',7,16),(549,'Calculate: 18 ÷ 3 × 2','multiple_choice',1,1,'Division and multiplication are done left to right. 18 ÷ 3 = 6, then 6 × 2 = 12.','','2025-11-15 08:50:52.548000','2026-02-14 00:02:13.492000',7,16),(550,'Evaluate: (12 - 4)² ÷ 8','multiple_choice',1,1,'Brackets first: (12 - 4) = 8. Then 8² = 64, and 64 ÷ 8 = 8.','','2025-11-15 08:50:52.652000','2026-02-14 00:02:13.649000',7,16),(551,'Evaluate: 5 × (9 - 3) + 2²','multiple_choice',1,1,'Brackets first: (9 - 3) = 6. Then 5 × 6 = 30, and 2² = 4. Finally 30 + 4 = 34.','','2025-11-15 08:50:52.749000','2026-02-14 00:02:13.802000',7,16),(552,'I think of a number. If I divide it by 4 and then add 7, the result is 12. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 12 - 7 = 5, then 5 × 4 = 20. So the number was 20.','','2025-11-15 08:50:52.850000','2026-02-14 00:02:13.937000',7,16),(553,'Calculate: 3 × (6 + 2) - 4²','multiple_choice',1,1,'Brackets first: (6 + 2) = 8. Then 3 × 8 = 24, and 4² = 16. Finally 24 - 16 = 8.','','2025-11-15 08:50:52.948000','2026-02-14 00:02:14.067000',7,16),(554,'Evaluate: 2³ + (10 - 4) × 2','multiple_choice',1,1,'Powers first: 2³ = 8. Brackets next: (10 - 4) = 6. Then 6 × 2 = 12. Finally 8 + 12 = 20.','','2025-11-15 08:50:53.072000','2026-02-14 00:02:14.200000',7,16),(555,'I think of a number. If I add 9, multiply by 2, and subtract 5, I get 31. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 31 + 5 = 36, then 36 ÷ 2 = 18, then 18 - 9 = 9. So the number was 9.','','2025-11-15 08:50:53.174000','2026-02-14 00:02:14.331000',7,16),(556,'Calculate: (3 + 5) × (2 + 6)','multiple_choice',1,1,'Brackets first: (3 + 5) = 8 and (2 + 6) = 8. Then 8 × 8 = 64.','','2025-11-15 08:50:53.273000','2026-02-14 00:02:14.478000',7,16),(557,'Evaluate: (9 - 3)² ÷ 9','multiple_choice',1,1,'Brackets first: (9 - 3) = 6. Then 6² = 36. Finally 36 ÷ 9 = 4.','','2025-11-15 08:50:53.374000','2026-02-14 00:02:14.624000',7,16),(558,'I think of a number. I multiply it by 5, then divide by 2, and finally subtract 10. The result is 15. What was the number I thought of?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Work backwards: 15 + 10 = 25, then 25 × 2 = 50, then 50 ÷ 5 = 10.','','2025-11-15 08:50:53.481000','2026-02-14 00:02:14.779000',7,16),(559,'Evaluate: 10 + (6 × 3) - 4²','multiple_choice',1,1,'Brackets first: (6 × 3) = 18. Then powers: 4² = 16. Finally 10 + 18 - 16 = 12.','','2025-11-15 08:50:53.584000','2026-02-14 00:02:14.911000',7,16),(560,'1 + 2 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2025-11-27 04:43:29.020000','2025-11-27 04:43:29.020000',11,9),(561,'1 + 5 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2025-11-27 04:43:29.065000','2025-11-27 04:43:29.065000',11,9),(562,'4 + 2 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2025-11-27 04:43:29.103000','2025-11-27 04:43:29.103000',11,9),(563,'2 + 1 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2025-11-27 04:43:29.146000','2025-11-27 04:43:29.146000',11,9),(564,'4 + 1 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2025-11-27 04:43:29.196000','2025-11-27 04:43:29.196000',11,9),(565,'4 + 3 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2025-11-27 04:43:29.245000','2025-11-27 04:43:29.245000',11,9),(566,'4 + 5 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2025-11-27 04:43:29.286000','2025-11-27 04:43:29.287000',11,9),(567,'0 + 4 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2025-11-27 04:43:29.336000','2025-11-27 04:43:29.336000',12,9),(568,'6 + 5 = ?','sh