ear6/measurements/image19.png','2026-02-06 11:03:15.118000','2026-02-06 11:03:15.142000',6,1),(1455,'Calculate the area of this shape.','multiple_choice',1,1,'Calculate the area of the triangle using 1/2 x base x height.','questions/year6/measurements/image20.png','2026-02-06 11:03:15.295000','2026-02-06 11:03:15.318000',6,1),(1456,'Calculate the area of this shape.','multiple_choice',1,1,'Calculate the rectangle area and remove the triangle area. (area of triangle is 1/2 x base x height).','questions/year6/measurements/image21.png','2026-02-06 11:03:15.477000','2026-02-06 11:03:15.504000',6,1),(1457,'The width of a cube increases by 50%, but it remains a cube. What is the percentage increase in the surface area of the cube?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the original side length of the cube = x, Original surface area = 6𝑥². New side length = 1.5𝑥, New surface area = 6(1.5𝑥)² = 13.5𝑥². Percentage increase = (New surface area - Original surface area) / Original surface area * 100% = (13.5𝑥² - 6𝑥²) / 6𝑥² * 100% = 125%.','','2026-02-06 11:03:15.753000','2026-02-06 11:03:15.753000',6,1),(1458,'The sides of a square are doubled. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the side = x, original area = x². New side = 2x, new area = (2x)² = 4x². Percentage increase = (4x² - x²) / x² × 100 = 300%.','','2026-02-06 11:03:15.939000','2026-02-06 11:03:15.939000',6,1),(1459,'The radius of a circle increases by 20%. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². If radius increases by 20%, new radius = 1.2r. New area = (1.2r)² = 1.44r², meaning a 44% increase.','','2026-02-06 11:03:16.142000','2026-02-06 11:03:16.142000',6,1),(1460,'The height of a cylinder is doubled and the radius is halved. What happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume = πr²h. New volume = π(½r)²(2h) = πr²h. The volume remains unchanged.','','2026-02-06 11:03:16.342000','2026-02-06 11:03:16.342000',6,1),(1461,'The length of a rectangle is increased by 50%, and the width stays the same. What is the percentage increase in area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area = L × W. Increasing length by 50% makes it 1.5L, so new area = 1.5LW. Increase = 50%.','','2026-02-06 11:03:16.535000','2026-02-06 11:03:16.535000',6,1),(1462,'A cube’s edge length is tripled. By what factor does its volume increase?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. If side is tripled, volume increases by 3³ = 27 times.','','2026-02-06 11:03:16.727000','2026-02-06 11:03:16.727000',6,1),(1463,'All dimensions of a rectangular prism are reduced by 50%. What is the percentage decrease in its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ length × width × height. If each is halved, new volume = (0.5)³ = 0.125, meaning 12.5% remains, so an 87.5% decrease.','','2026-02-06 11:03:16.917000','2026-02-06 11:03:16.917000',6,1),(1464,'The diameter of a circle is reduced by 40%. What is the percentage decrease in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². New radius = 0.6r, new area = 0.36r² → area decreases by 64%.','','2026-02-06 11:03:17.101000','2026-02-06 11:03:17.101000',6,1),(1465,'The volume of a cube doubles. What is the percentage increase in the cube’s side length?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = ³√2 × old side ≈ 1.26×, which is a 26% increase.','','2026-02-06 11:03:17.288000','2026-02-06 11:03:17.288000',6,1),(1466,'A rectangle’s perimeter is 60 cm. If both its length and width increase by 25%, what is the new perimeter?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Perimeter ∝ (L + W). If both increase by 25%, total perimeter increases by 25% → 60 × 1.25 = 75 cm.','','2026-02-06 11:03:17.482000','2026-02-06 11:03:17.482000',6,1),(1467,'The surface area of a cube is 150 cm². If the edge length doubles, what is the new surface area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Surface area ∝ side². Doubling the side makes the area 4 times larger → 150 × 4 = 600 cm².','','2026-02-06 11:03:17.691000','2026-02-06 11:03:17.691000',6,1),(1468,'A cube-shaped gift box has a side length of 10 cm. If the side is increased by 20%, what is the new volume of the box compared to the old one?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = 1.2× old side, so new volume = (1.2)³ = 1.728× the original.','','2026-02-06 11:03:17.902000','2026-02-06 11:03:17.902000',6,1),(1469,'A rectangular water tank is 2 m long, 1.5 m wide, and 1 m high. If the height is doubled, how much more water can it hold?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles the capacity → 2× the amount of water.','','2026-02-06 11:03:18.097000','2026-02-06 11:03:18.097000',6,1),(1470,'A cylindrical candle has a radius of 5 cm and height of 10 cm. If the radius is doubled and height stays the same, how many times greater is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cylinder = πr²h. Doubling radius makes r² → (2r)² = 4r² → volume increases 4 times.','','2026-02-06 11:03:18.294000','2026-02-06 11:03:18.294000',6,1),(1471,'A cone has a radius of 3 cm and height of 8 cm. If both radius and height are doubled, how many times greater is the volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h. If both r and h double → (2r)²(2h) = 8× bigger.','','2026-02-06 11:03:18.503000','2026-02-06 11:03:18.503000',6,1),(1472,'A cylindrical water bottle has a volume of 500 mL. If its height is doubled but the radius stays the same, what will the new volume be?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles volume → 500 mL × 2 = 1 L.','','2026-02-06 11:03:18.708000','2026-02-06 11:03:18.708000',6,1),(1473,'A metal cube is melted and reshaped into a cylinder with the same volume. If the cube’s side is 6 cm, what is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cube = side³ = 6³ = 216 cm³.','','2026-02-06 11:03:18.919000','2026-02-06 11:03:18.919000',6,1),(1474,'A cone and a cylinder have the same base radius and height. How does the volume of the cone compare to the cylinder?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h, while cylinder = πr²h. Therefore, cone = one-third of the cylinder.','','2026-02-06 11:03:19.111000','2026-02-06 11:03:19.112000',6,1),(1475,'A cylindrical jar has a radius of 4 cm and height of 12 cm. If both radius and height increase by 25%, how many times larger is the new volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. New radius = 1.25r, new height = 1.25h → new volume = (1.25)³ = 1.953× larger.','','2026-02-06 11:03:19.286000','2026-02-06 11:03:19.286000',6,1),(1476,'A swimming pool is shaped like a rectangular prism 8 m long, 4 m wide, and 2 m deep. If it is filled halfway, how much water is inside?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Full volume = 8×4×2 = 64 m³. Half full = 64 ÷ 2 = 32 m³.','','2026-02-06 11:03:19.469000','2026-02-06 11:03:19.469000',6,1),(1477,'A cone-shaped paper cup has a height of 9 cm and radius of 3 cm. If both dimensions are halved, what happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. If r and h are halved → (½)³ = ⅛ → volume becomes one-eighth.','','2026-02-06 11:03:19.663000','2026-02-06 11:03:19.663000',6,1),(1478,'3 + 5 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 11:06:42.398000','2026-02-06 11:06:42.398000',11,9),(1479,'2 + 2 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 11:06:42.459000','2026-02-06 11:06:42.459000',11,9),(1480,'5 + 2 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 11:06:42.527000','2026-02-06 11:06:42.527000',11,9),(1481,'5 + 4 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 11:06:42.603000','2026-02-06 11:06:42.603000',12,9),(1482,'9 + 9 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 11:06:42.670000','2026-02-06 11:06:42.670000',12,9),(1483,'1 + 6 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 11:06:42.734000','2026-02-06 11:06:42.734000',12,9),(1484,'4 + 7 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 11:06:42.796000','2026-02-06 11:06:42.796000',12,9),(1485,'3 + 4 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 11:06:42.866000','2026-02-06 11:06:42.866000',12,9),(1486,'3 + 9 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 11:06:42.925000','2026-02-06 11:06:42.925000',12,9),(1487,'9 