ing a 44% increase.','','2026-02-06 12:37:02.068000','2026-02-06 12:37:02.068000',6,1),(1850,'The height of a cylinder is doubled and the radius is halved. What happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume = πr²h. New volume = π(½r)²(2h) = πr²h. The volume remains unchanged.','','2026-02-06 12:37:02.259000','2026-02-06 12:37:02.259000',6,1),(1851,'The length of a rectangle is increased by 50%, and the width stays the same. What is the percentage increase in area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area = L × W. Increasing length by 50% makes it 1.5L, so new area = 1.5LW. Increase = 50%.','','2026-02-06 12:37:02.460000','2026-02-06 12:37:02.461000',6,1),(1852,'A cube’s edge length is tripled. By what factor does its volume increase?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. If side is tripled, volume increases by 3³ = 27 times.','','2026-02-06 12:37:02.650000','2026-02-06 12:37:02.650000',6,1),(1853,'All dimensions of a rectangular prism are reduced by 50%. What is the percentage decrease in its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ length × width × height. If each is halved, new volume = (0.5)³ = 0.125, meaning 12.5% remains, so an 87.5% decrease.','','2026-02-06 12:37:02.861000','2026-02-06 12:37:02.861000',6,1),(1854,'The diameter of a circle is reduced by 40%. What is the percentage decrease in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². New radius = 0.6r, new area = 0.36r² → area decreases by 64%.','','2026-02-06 12:37:03.064000','2026-02-06 12:37:03.065000',6,1),(1855,'The volume of a cube doubles. What is the percentage increase in the cube’s side length?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = ³√2 × old side ≈ 1.26×, which is a 26% increase.','','2026-02-06 12:37:03.271000','2026-02-06 12:37:03.271000',6,1),(1856,'A rectangle’s perimeter is 60 cm. If both its length and width increase by 25%, what is the new perimeter?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Perimeter ∝ (L + W). If both increase by 25%, total perimeter increases by 25% → 60 × 1.25 = 75 cm.','','2026-02-06 12:37:03.474000','2026-02-06 12:37:03.474000',6,1),(1857,'The surface area of a cube is 150 cm². If the edge length doubles, what is the new surface area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Surface area ∝ side². Doubling the side makes the area 4 times larger → 150 × 4 = 600 cm².','','2026-02-06 12:37:03.672000','2026-02-06 12:37:03.672000',6,1),(1858,'A cube-shaped gift box has a side length of 10 cm. If the side is increased by 20%, what is the new volume of the box compared to the old one?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = 1.2× old side, so new volume = (1.2)³ = 1.728× the original.','','2026-02-06 12:37:03.886000','2026-02-06 12:37:03.886000',6,1),(1859,'A rectangular water tank is 2 m long, 1.5 m wide, and 1 m high. If the height is doubled, how much more water can it hold?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles the capacity → 2× the amount of water.','','2026-02-06 12:37:04.121000','2026-02-06 12:37:04.121000',6,1),(1860,'A cylindrical candle has a radius of 5 cm and height of 10 cm. If the radius is doubled and height stays the same, how many times greater is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cylinder = πr²h. Doubling radius makes r² → (2r)² = 4r² → volume increases 4 times.','','2026-02-06 12:37:04.365000','2026-02-06 12:37:04.365000',6,1),(1861,'A cone has a radius of 3 cm and height of 8 cm. If both radius and height are doubled, how many times greater is the volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h. If both r and h double → (2r)²(2h) = 8× bigger.','','2026-02-06 12:37:04.556000','2026-02-06 12:37:04.556000',6,1),(1862,'A cylindrical water bottle has a volume of 500 mL. If its height is doubled but the radius stays the same, what will the new volume be?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles volume → 500 mL × 2 = 1 L.','','2026-02-06 12:37:04.741000','2026-02-06 12:37:04.741000',6,1),(1863,'A metal cube is melted and reshaped into a cylinder with the same volume. If the cube’s side is 6 cm, what is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cube = side³ = 6³ = 216 cm³.','','2026-02-06 12:37:04.921000','2026-02-06 12:37:04.921000',6,1),(1864,'A cone and a cylinder have the same base radius and height. How does the volume of the cone compare to the cylinder?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h, while cylinder = πr²h. Therefore, cone = one-third of the cylinder.','','2026-02-06 12:37:05.104000','2026-02-06 12:37:05.104000',6,1),(1865,'A cylindrical jar has a radius of 4 cm and height of 12 cm. If both radius and height increase by 25%, how many times larger is the new volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. New radius = 1.25r, new height = 1.25h → new volume = (1.25)³ = 1.953× larger.','','2026-02-06 12:37:05.285000','2026-02-06 12:37:05.285000',6,1),(1866,'A swimming pool is shaped like a rectangular prism 8 m long, 4 m wide, and 2 m deep. If it is filled halfway, how much water is inside?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Full volume = 8×4×2 = 64 m³. Half full = 64 ÷ 2 = 32 m³.','','2026-02-06 12:37:05.464000','2026-02-06 12:37:05.465000',6,1),(1867,'A cone-shaped paper cup has a height of 9 cm and radius of 3 cm. If both dimensions are halved, what happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. If r and h are halved → (½)³ = ⅛ → volume becomes one-eighth.','','2026-02-06 12:37:05.643000','2026-02-06 12:37:05.643000',6,1),(1868,'6 × 1000 + 3 × 10 + 2 × 1 is the expanded form of:','Multiple Choice',2,1,'The expanded form 6 × 1000 + 3 × 10 + 2 × 1 represents the number 6032. This is calculated by multiplying each digit by its place value and then adding them together: (6 × 1000) + (3 × 10) + (2 × 1) = 6000 + 30 + 2 = 6032.','','2026-02-06 12:37:17.229000','2026-02-14 00:02:19.383000',7,23),(1869,'What is the place value of the digit 5 in 856?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'In the number 856, the digit 5 is in the tens place. Therefore, its place value is 5 × 10 = 50. The other options are incorrect: 500 is the place value of the digit 8, 5 is the place value of the digit 6, and 5000 is the place value of the digit 8 in a different number.','','2026-02-06 12:37:18.012000','2026-02-14 00:02:20.240000',7,23),(1870,'What is the place value of the digit 5 in 1544?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'In the number 1544, the digit 5 is in the hundreds place. Therefore, its place value is 5 × 100 = 500. The other options are incorrect: 50 is the place value of the digit 4 in the tens place, 5 is the place value of the digit 4 in the ones place, and 5000 is the place value of the digit 1 in the thousands place.','','2026-02-06 12:37:18.118000','2026-02-14 00:02:20.393000',7,23),(1871,'A car\'s odometer shows 7854 kilometres at the start of a journey. When the driver stops for lunch, the odometer reads 8012 kilometres. How far has the car travelled?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'The distance travelled by the car is calculated by subtracting the starting odometer reading from the ending odometer reading: 8012 km - 7854 km = 158 km. The other options are incorrect: 1580 kilometres is ten times the correct answer, 15800 kilometres is one hundred times the correct answer, and 15.8 kilometres is one tenth of the correct answer.','','2026-02-06 12:37:19.105000','2026-02-14 00:02:21.375000',7,23),(1872,'A car\'s odometer shows 7854 kilometres at the start of a journey. What will the car\'s odometer read if the car then travels a further 59 kilometres?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'The car\'s odometer will read 7854 km + 59 km = 7913 km. The other options are incorrect: 7903 kilometres is 51 km less than the correct answer, 7923 kilometres is 9 km more than the correct answer, and 7803 kilometres is 51 km less than the correct answer.','','2026-02-06 12:37:19.207000','2026-02-14 00:02:21.513000',7,23),(1873,'The sum of 13 and double 7 is multiplied by 100','Multiple Choice',2,1,'The sum of 13 and double 7 is 13 + (2 × 7) = 13 + 14 = 27. When this is multiplied by 100, the result is 27 × 100 = 2700. The other options are incorrect: 2600 is one hundred less than the correct answer, 2800 is one hundred more than the correct answer, and 270 is one tenth of the correct answer.','','2026-02-06 12:37:19.311000','2026-02-14 00:02:21.654000',7,23),(1874,'3 + 2 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:17.946000','2026-02-06 12:38:17.946000',11,9),(1875,'5 + 3 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:18.055000','2026-02-06 12:38:18.055000',11,9),(1876,'0 + 3 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:18.126000','2026-02-06 12:38:18.126000',12,9),(1877,'5 + 0 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:18.179000','2026-02-06 12:38:18.179000',12,9),(1878,'9 + 2 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:18.233000','2026-02-06 12:38:18.233000',12,9),(1879,'8 + 1 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:18.284000','2026-02-06 12:38:18.284000',12,9),(1880,'2 + 2 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:18.332000','2026-02-06 12:38:18.332000',12,9),(1881,'7 + 2 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:18.381000','2026-02-06 12:38:18.381000',12,9),(1882,'8 + 3 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:18.453000','2026-02-06 12:38:18.453000',12,9),(1883,'42 + 21 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:18.526000','2026-02-06 12:38:18.526000',13,9),(1884,'31 + 17 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:18.586000','2026-02-06 12:38:18.586000',13,9),(1885,'41 + 11 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:18.633000','2026-02-06 12:38:18.633000',13,9),(1886,'32 + 32 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:18.689000','2026-02-06 12:38:18.689000',13,9),(1887,'33 + 12 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:18.742000','2026-02-06 12:38:18.742000',13,9),(1888,'13 + 13 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:18.792000','2026-02-06 12:38:18.792000',13,9),(1889,'32 + 24 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:18.846000','2026-02-06 12:38:18.846000',13,9),(1890,'14 + 34 = ?','short_answer',1