1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:27.054000','2026-02-06 12:38:27.054000',37,12),(2017,'264 ÷ 4 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:27.109000','2026-02-06 12:38:27.109000',37,12),(2018,'34 ÷ 2 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:27.151000','2026-02-06 12:38:27.151000',37,12),(2019,'504 ÷ 6 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:27.200000','2026-02-06 12:38:27.200000',37,12),(2020,'189 ÷ 7 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:27.260000','2026-02-06 12:38:27.260000',38,12),(2021,'42 ÷ 3 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:27.309000','2026-02-06 12:38:27.309000',38,12),(2022,'162 ÷ 2 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:27.361000','2026-02-06 12:38:27.361000',38,12),(2023,'399 ÷ 7 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:27.410000','2026-02-06 12:38:27.410000',38,12),(2024,'510 ÷ 6 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:27.463000','2026-02-06 12:38:27.463000',38,12),(2025,'438 ÷ 6 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:27.514000','2026-02-06 12:38:27.514000',38,12),(2026,'360 ÷ 4 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:27.567000','2026-02-06 12:38:27.567000',38,12),(2027,'847 ÷ 11 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:27.622000','2026-02-06 12:38:27.622000',38,12),(2028,'264 ÷ 8 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:27.675000','2026-02-06 12:38:27.675000',38,12),(2029,'728 ÷ 8 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-06 12:38:27.731000','2026-02-06 12:38:27.731000',38,12),(2030,'Calculate the area of this shape.','multiple_choice',1,1,'Calculate the area using πr².','questions/year6/measurements/image9.png','2026-02-06 12:38:37.655000','2026-02-06 12:38:37.681000',6,1),(2031,'The width of a cube increases by 50%, but it remains a cube. What is the percentage increase in the surface area of the cube?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the original side length of the cube = x, Original surface area = 6𝑥². New side length = 1.5𝑥, New surface area = 6(1.5𝑥)² = 13.5𝑥². Percentage increase = (New surface area - Original surface area) / Original surface area * 100% = (13.5𝑥² - 6𝑥²) / 6𝑥² * 100% = 125%.','','2026-02-06 12:38:38.266000','2026-02-06 12:38:38.266000',6,1),(2032,'The sides of a square are doubled. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the side = x, original area = x². New side = 2x, new area = (2x)² = 4x². Percentage increase = (4x² - x²) / x² × 100 = 300%.','','2026-02-06 12:38:38.468000','2026-02-06 12:38:38.468000',6,1),(2033,'The radius of a circle increases by 20%. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². If radius increases by 20%, new radius = 1.2r. New area = (1.2r)² = 1.44r², meaning a 44% increase.','','2026-02-06 12:38:38.648000','2026-02-06 12:38:38.648000',6,1),(2034,'The height of a cylinder is doubled and the radius is halved. What happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume = πr²h. New volume = π(½r)²(2h) = πr²h. The volume remains unchanged.','','2026-02-06 12:38:38.827000','2026-02-06 12:38:38.827000',6,1),(2035,'The length of a rectangle is increased by 50%, and the width stays the same. What is the percentage increase in area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area = L × W. Increasing length by 50% makes it 1.5L, so new area = 1.5LW. Increase = 50%.','','2026-02-06 12:38:39.022000','2026-02-06 12:38:39.022000',6,1),(2036,'A cube’s edge length is tripled. By what factor does its volume increase?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. If side is tripled, volume increases by 3³ = 27 times.','','2026-02-06 12:38:39.205000','2026-02-06 12:38:39.205000',6,1),(2037,'All dimensions of a rectangular prism are reduced by 50%. What is the percentage decrease in its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ length × width × height. If each is halved, new volume = (0.5)³ = 0.125, meaning 12.5% remains, so an 87.5% decrease.','','2026-02-06 12:38:39.394000','2026-02-06 12:38:39.394000',6,1),(2038,'The diameter of a circle is reduced by 40%. What is the percentage decrease in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². New radius = 0.6r, new area = 0.36r² → area decreases by 64%.','','2026-02-06 12:38:39.577000','2026-02-06 12:38:39.577000',6,1),(2039,'The volume of a cube doubles. What is the percentage increase in the cube’s side length?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = ³√2 × old side ≈ 1.26×, which is a 26% increase.','','2026-02-06 12:38:39.758000','2026-02-06 12:38:39.758000',6,1),(2040,'A rectangle’s perimeter is 60 cm. If both its length and width increase by 25%, what is the new perimeter?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Perimeter ∝ (L + W). If both increase by 25%, total perimeter increases by 25% → 60 × 1.25 = 75 cm.','','2026-02-06 12:38:39.942000','2026-02-06 12:38:39.942000',6,1),(2041,'The surface area of a cube is 150 cm². If the edge length doubles, what is the new surface area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Surface area ∝ side². Doubling the side makes the area 4 times larger → 150 × 4 = 600 cm².','','2026-02-06 12:38:40.114000','2026-02-06 12:38:40.114000',6,1),(2042,'A cube-shaped gift box has a side length of 10 cm. If the side is increased by 20%, what is the new volume of the box compared to the old one?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = 1.2× old side, so new volume = (1.2)³ = 1.728× the original.','','2026-02-06 12:38:40.307000','2026-02-06 12:38:40.307000',6,1),(2043,'A rectangular water tank is 2 m long, 1.5 m wide, and 1 m high. If the height is doubled, how much more water can it hold?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles the capacity → 2× the amount of water.','','2026-02-06 12:38:40.492000','2026-02-06 12:38:40.492000',6,1),(2044,'A cylindrical candle has a radius of 5 cm and height of 10 cm. If the radius is doubled and height stays the same, how many times greater is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cylinder = πr²h. Doubling radius makes r² → (2r)² = 4r² → volume increases 4 times.','','2026-02-06 12:38:40.684000','2026-02-06 12:38:40.684000',6,1),(2045,'A cone has a radius of 3 cm and height of 8 cm. If both radius and height are doubled, how many times greater is the volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h. If both r and h double → (2r)²(2h) = 8× bigger.','','2026-02-06 12:38:40.854000','2026-02-06 12:38:40.854000',6,1),(2046,'A cylindrical water bottle has a volume of 500 mL. If its height is doubled but the radius stays the same, what will the new volume be?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles volume → 500 mL × 2 = 1 L.','','2026-02-06 12:38:41.042000','2026-02-06 12:38:41.042000',6,1),(2047,'A metal cube is melted and reshaped into a cylinder with the same volume. If the cube’s side is 6 cm, what is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cube = side³ = 6³ = 216 cm³.','','2026-02-06 12:38:41.240000','2026-02-06 12:38:41.240000',6,1),(2048,'A cone and a cylinder have the same base radius and height. How does the volume of the cone compare to the cylinder?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h, while cylinder = πr²h. Therefore, cone = one-third of the cylinder.','','2026-02-06 12:38:41.424000','2026-02-06 12:38:41.424000',6,1),(2049,'A cylindrical jar has a radius of 4 cm and height of 12 cm. If both radius and height increase by 25%, how many times larger is the new volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. New radius = 1.25r, new height = 1.25h → new volume = (1.25)³ = 1.953× larger.','','2026-02-06 12:38:41.612000','2026-02-06 12:38:41.613000',6,1),(2050,'A swimming pool is shaped like a rectangular prism 8 m long, 4 m wide, and 2 m deep. If it is filled halfway, how much water is inside?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Full volume = 8×4×2 = 64 m³. Half full = 64 ÷ 2 = 32 m³.','','2026-02-06 12:38:41.793000','2026-02-06 12:38:41.793000',6,1),(2051,'A cone-shaped paper cup has a height of 9 cm and radius of 3 cm. If both dimensions are halved, what happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. If r and h are halved → (½)³ = ⅛ → volume becomes one-eighth.','','2026-02-06 12:38:41.979000','2026-02-06 12:38:41.979000',6,1),(2052,'In a right-angled triangle, the trigonometric ratio for opposite divided by hypotenuse is called:','Multiple Choice',2,1,'The sine ratio is defined as opposite/hypotenuse. This is part of SOHCAHTOA: Sine = Opposite/Hypotenuse.','','2026-02-06 12:38:59.161000','2026-02-14 00:02:28.344000',8,24),(2053,'What does the acronym SOHCAHTOA stand for in trigonometry?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'SOHCAHTOA is a mnemonic for remembering the three basic trigonometric ratios in a right-angled triangle.','','2026-02-06 12:38:59.306000','2026-02-14 00:02:28.480000',8,24),(2054,'In a right-angled triangle, the cosine ratio is:','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Cosine is defined as the ratio of the adjacent side to the hypotenuse (COH in SOHCAHTOA).','','2026-02-06 12:38:59.437000','2026-02-14 00:02:28.613000',8,24),(2055,'The tangent of an angle in a right-angled triangle is:','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Tangent is defined as the ratio of the opposite side to the adjacent side (TOA in SOHCAHTOA).','','2026-02-06 12:38:59.568000','2026-02-14 00:02:28.739000',8,24),(2056,'What is the approximate value of sin(30°)?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'The sine of 30 degrees is 0.5 (or 1/2). This is one of the standard trigonometric values.','','2026-02-06 12:38:59.702000','2026-02-14 00:02:28.885000',8,24),(2057,'What is the approximate value of cos(60°)?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'The cosine of 60 degrees is 0.5 (or 1/2). This is one of the standard trigonometric values.','','2026-02-06 12:38:59.828000','2026-02-14 00:02:29.040000',8,24),(2058,'What is the approximate value of sin(45°)?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'The sine of 45 degrees is approximately 0.707 (or √2/2). This is one of the standard trigonometric values.','','2026-02-06 12:38:59.953000','2026-02-14 00:02:29.185000',8,24),(2059,'What is the approximate value of cos(45°)?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'The cosine of 45 degrees is approximately 0.707 (or √2/2). This is one of the standard trigonometric values.','','2026-02-06 12:39:00.075000','2026-02-14 00:02:29.317000',8,24),(2060,'What is the approximate value of tan(45°)?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'The tangent of 45 degrees is exactly 1. This is because at 45 degrees, the opposite and adjacent sides are equal.','','2026-02-06 12:39:00.206000','2026-02-14 00:02:29.447000',8,24),(2061,'Find the value of X in these right-angled triangles, correct to two decimal places (cos(38°) = 0.7880)','Multiple Choice',2,1,'cos(38°) = adjacent/hypotenuse = X/14 ≈ 11.03 m.','','2026-02-06 12:39:00.348000','2026-02-14 00:02:29.580000',8,24),(2062,'Find the value of X in these right-angled triangles, correct to two decimal places (tan(38°) = 2.6051)','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using tan(38°) = opposite/adjacent: opposite = 25 × tan(38°) ≈ 25 × 2.6051 ≈ 61.88 m.','','2026-02-06 12:39:00.479000','2026-02-14 00:02:29.709000',8,24),(2063,'In a right-angled triangle with angle of 60°, hypotenuse of 20 cm, what is the length of the adjacent side?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using cos(60°) = adjacent/hypotenuse: adjacent = 20 × cos(60°) = 20 × 0.5 = 10 cm.','','2026-02-06 12:39:00.612000','2026-02-14 00:02:29.858000',8,24),(2064,'A ladder leans against a wall at an angle of 60° to the ground. If the ladder is 8 metres long, how high does it reach up the wall?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using sin(60°) = height/hypotenuse: height = 8 × sin(60°) = 8 × 0.866 = 6.93 metres approximately.','','2026-02-06 12:39:00.742000','2026-02-14 00:02:30.004000',8,24),(2065,'Which trigonometric ratio would you use to find the angle if you know the opposite and adjacent sides?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'When you know opposite and adjacent sides, you use tan⁻¹ (arctan or inverse tangent) to find the angle.','','2026-02-06 12:39:00.872000','2026-02-14 00:02:30.149000',8,24),(2066,'In a right-angled triangle, if the opposite side is 5 cm and the adjacent side is 5 cm, what is the angle?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'When opposite = adjacent, the ratio is 1, so tan(angle) = 1, which means angle = 45°.','','2026-02-06 12:39:01.015000','2026-02-14 00:02:30.297000',8,24),(2067,'In a right-angled triangle, if the opposite side is 8 cm and the hypotenuse is 16 cm, what is the angle?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using sin(angle) = opposite/hypotenuse = 8/16 = 0.5, and sin(30°) = 0.5, the angle is 30°.','','2026-02-06 12:39:01.153000','2026-02-14 00:02:30.442000',8,24),(2068,'In a right-angled triangle, if the adjacent side is 5 cm and the hypotenuse is 10 cm, what is the angle?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using cos(angle) = adjacent/hypotenuse = 5/10 = 0.5, and cos(60°) = 0.5, the angle is 60°.','','2026-02-06 12:39:01.285000','2026-02-14 00:02:30.582000',8,24),(2069,'In a right-angled triangle, if the opposite side is 10 cm and the adjacent side is 10√3 cm, what is the angle? (tan(30°) = 0.577), tan(60°) = 1.732, tan(45°) = 1, tan(90°) = infinity','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using tan(angle) = opposite/adjacent = 10/(10√3) = 1/√3 ≈ 0.577, and tan(30°) ≈ 0.577, the angle is 30°.','','2026-02-06 12:39:01.426000','2026-02-14 00:02:30.735000',8,24),(2070,'A ramp makes an angle of 25° with the ground. If the ramp is 10 metres long, what is the vertical height? (sin(25°) = 0.423)','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using sin(25°) = height/hypotenuse: height = 10 × sin(25°) = 10 × 0.423 = 4.23 metres.','','2026-02-06 12:39:01.565000','2026-02-14 00:02:30.889000',8,24),(2071,'From a point on the ground 50 metres away from a tower, the angle of elevation to the top is 35°. What is the height of the tower? (tan(35°) = 0.700)','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using tan(35°) = height/distance: height = 50 × tan(35°) = 50 × 0.700 = 35 metres.','','2026-02-06 12:39:01.708000','2026-02-14 00:02:31.050000',8,24),(2072,'An airplane is flying at a height of 3000 metres. The angle of depression to a point on the ground is 28°. What is the horizontal distance? (tan(28°) = 0.532)','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using tan(28°) = height/distance: distance = 3000 / tan(28°) = 3000 / 0.532 ≈ 5639 metres.','','2026-02-06 12:39:01.843000','2026-02-14 00:02:31.199000',8,24),(2073,'In a right-angled triangle, if sin(θ) = 0.8, what is tan(θ)?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'If sin(θ) = 0.8, then cos(θ) = 0.6 (from sin²θ + cos²θ = 1). Then tan(θ) = sin(θ)/cos(θ) = 0.8/0.6 = 4/3 ≈ 1.33.','','2026-02-06 12:39:01.976000','2026-02-14 00:02:31.366000',8,24),(2074,'A ladder of 15 metres is placed against a wall such that the angle between the ladder and the ground is 65°. How high does the ladder reach on the wall? (sin(65°) = 0.906)','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using sin(65°) = height/hypotenuse: height = 15 × sin(65°) = 15 × 0.906 = 13.59 metres.','','2026-02-06 12:39:02.103000','2026-02-14 00:02:31.501000',8,24),(2075,'If a trigonometric angle has cos(θ) = 0.6, what is sin(θ)?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using sin²(θ) + cos²(θ) = 1: sin²(θ) = 1 - 0.36 = 0.64, so sin(θ) = 0.8.','','2026-02-06 12:39:02.235000','2026-02-14 00:02:31.655000',8,24),(2076,'What is sin(90°)?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'The sine of 90 degrees is 1. At 90 degrees, the opposite side equals the hypotenuse.','','2026-02-06 12:39:02.367000','2026-02-14 00:02:33.413000',8,24),(2077,'What is cos(0°)?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'The cosine of 0 degrees is 1. At 0 degrees, the adjacent side equals the hypotenuse.','','2026-02-06 12:39:02.505000','2026-02-14 00:02:33.553000',8,24),(2078,'What is tan(0°)?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'The tangent of 0 degrees is 0. At 0 degrees, the opposite side has length 0.','','2026-02-06 12:39:02.632000','2026-02-14 00:02:33.687000',8,24),(2079,'In a right-angled triangle, if sin(θ) = 0.6, which trigonometric value is cos(θ)?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using sin²(θ) + cos²(θ) = 1: cos²(θ) = 1 - 0.36 = 0.64, so cos(θ) = 0.8.','','2026-02-06 12:39:02.757000','2026-02-14 00:02:33.821000',8,24),(2080,'A surveyor measures an angle of elevation of 30° to the top of a building from a distance of 100 metres. What is the approximate height of the building? (tan(30°) = 0.577)','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using tan(30°) = height/distance: height = 100 × tan(30°) = 100 × 0.577 = 57.7 metres approximately.','','2026-02-06 12:39:02.881000','2026-02-14 00:02:33.943000',8,24),(2081,'Which angle has a sine value of approximately 0.866?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'sin(60°) ≈ 0.866 (or √3/2). This is one of the standard trigonometric values.','','2026-02-06 12:39:03.009000','2026-02-14 00:02:34.088000',8,24),(2082,'4 + 9 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:08:50.254000','2026-02-13 10:08:50.254000',12,9),(2083,'6 + 9 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:08:50.308000','2026-02-13 10:08:50.309000',12,9),(2084,'7 + 8 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:08:50.354000','2026-02-13 10:08:50.354000',12,9),(2085,'5 + 7 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:08:50.407000','2026-02-13 10:08:50.407000',12,9),(2086,'3 + 1 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:08:50.457000','2026-02-13 10:08:50.457000',12,9),(2087,'4 + 6 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:08:50.510000','2026-02-13 10:08:50.510000',12,9),(2088,'4 + 2 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:08:50.560000','2026-02-13 10:08:50.560000',12,9),(2089,'43 + 40 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:08:50.628000','2026-02-13 10:08:50.628000',13,9),(2090,'24 + 32 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:08:50.677000','2026-02-13 10:08:50.677000',13,9),(2091,'31 + 27 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:08:50.727000','2026-02-13 10:08:50.727000',13,9),(2092,'30 + 19 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:08:50.784000','2026-02-13 10:08:50.784000',13,9),(2093,'10 + 46 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:08:50.831000','2026-02-13 10:08:50.831000',13,9),(2094,'30 + 31 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:08:50.879000','2026-02-13 10:08:50.879000',13,9),(2095,'11 + 25 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:08:50.924000','2026-02-13 10:08:50.924000',13,9),(2096,'23 + 35 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','