= ?','Multiple Choice',1,1,'45 minus 19 equals 26.','','2026-02-13 10:09:06.170000','2026-02-14 00:01:57.780000',4,23),(2240,'Calculate the area of this shape.','multiple_choice',1,1,'Calculate the area using πr².','questions/year6/measurements/image9.png','2026-02-13 10:09:08.854000','2026-02-13 10:09:08.879000',6,1),(2241,'The width of a cube increases by 50%, but it remains a cube. What is the percentage increase in the surface area of the cube?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the original side length of the cube = x, Original surface area = 6𝑥². New side length = 1.5𝑥, New surface area = 6(1.5𝑥)² = 13.5𝑥². Percentage increase = (New surface area - Original surface area) / Original surface area * 100% = (13.5𝑥² - 6𝑥²) / 6𝑥² * 100% = 125%.','','2026-02-13 10:09:09.397000','2026-02-13 10:09:09.397000',6,1),(2242,'The sides of a square are doubled. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the side = x, original area = x². New side = 2x, new area = (2x)² = 4x². Percentage increase = (4x² - x²) / x² × 100 = 300%.','','2026-02-13 10:09:09.569000','2026-02-13 10:09:09.569000',6,1),(2243,'The radius of a circle increases by 20%. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². If radius increases by 20%, new radius = 1.2r. New area = (1.2r)² = 1.44r², meaning a 44% increase.','','2026-02-13 10:09:09.743000','2026-02-13 10:09:09.743000',6,1),(2244,'The height of a cylinder is doubled and the radius is halved. What happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume = πr²h. New volume = π(½r)²(2h) = πr²h. The volume remains unchanged.','','2026-02-13 10:09:09.901000','2026-02-13 10:09:09.901000',6,1),(2245,'The length of a rectangle is increased by 50%, and the width stays the same. What is the percentage increase in area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area = L × W. Increasing length by 50% makes it 1.5L, so new area = 1.5LW. Increase = 50%.','','2026-02-13 10:09:10.065000','2026-02-13 10:09:10.065000',6,1),(2246,'A cube’s edge length is tripled. By what factor does its volume increase?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. If side is tripled, volume increases by 3³ = 27 times.','','2026-02-13 10:09:10.226000','2026-02-13 10:09:10.226000',6,1),(2247,'All dimensions of a rectangular prism are reduced by 50%. What is the percentage decrease in its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ length × width × height. If each is halved, new volume = (0.5)³ = 0.125, meaning 12.5% remains, so an 87.5% decrease.','','2026-02-13 10:09:10.390000','2026-02-13 10:09:10.390000',6,1),(2248,'The diameter of a circle is reduced by 40%. What is the percentage decrease in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². New radius = 0.6r, new area = 0.36r² → area decreases by 64%.','','2026-02-13 10:09:10.550000','2026-02-13 10:09:10.550000',6,1),(2249,'The volume of a cube doubles. What is the percentage increase in the cube’s side length?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = ³√2 × old side ≈ 1.26×, which is a 26% increase.','','2026-02-13 10:09:10.733000','2026-02-13 10:09:10.733000',6,1),(2250,'A rectangle’s perimeter is 60 cm. If both its length and width increase by 25%, what is the new perimeter?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Perimeter ∝ (L + W). If both increase by 25%, total perimeter increases by 25% → 60 × 1.25 = 75 cm.','','2026-02-13 10:09:10.900000','2026-02-13 10:09:10.900000',6,1),(2251,'The surface area of a cube is 150 cm². If the edge length doubles, what is the new surface area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Surface area ∝ side². Doubling the side makes the area 4 times larger → 150 × 4 = 600 cm².','','2026-02-13 10:09:11.083000','2026-02-13 10:09:11.083000',6,1),(2252,'A cube-shaped gift box has a side length of 10 cm. If the side is increased by 20%, what is the new volume of the box compared to the old one?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = 1.2× old side, so new volume = (1.2)³ = 1.728× the original.','','2026-02-13 10:09:11.249000','2026-02-13 10:09:11.249000',6,1),(2253,'A rectangular water tank is 2 m long, 1.5 m wide, and 1 m high. If the height is doubled, how much more water can it hold?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles the capacity → 2× the amount of water.','','2026-02-13 10:09:11.423000','2026-02-13 10:09:11.423000',6,1),(2254,'A cylindrical candle has a radius of 5 cm and height of 10 cm. If the radius is doubled and height stays the same, how many times greater is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cylinder = πr²h. Doubling radius makes r² → (2r)² = 4r² → volume increases 4 times.','','2026-02-13 10:09:11.599000','2026-02-13 10:09:11.599000',6,1),(2255,'A cone has a radius of 3 cm and height of 8 cm. If both radius and height are doubled, how many times greater is the volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h. If both r and h double → (2r)²(2h) = 8× bigger.','','2026-02-13 10:09:11.781000','2026-02-13 10:09:11.781000',6,1),(2256,'A cylindrical water bottle has a volume of 500 mL. If its height is doubled but the radius stays the same, what will the new volume be?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles volume → 500 mL × 2 = 1 L.','','2026-02-13 10:09:11.951000','2026-02-13 10:09:11.952000',6,1),(2257,'A metal cube is melted and reshaped into a cylinder with the same volume. If the cube’s side is 6 cm, what is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cube = side³ = 6³ = 216 cm³.','','2026-02-13 10:09:12.119000','2026-02-13 10:09:12.119000',6,1),(2258,'A cone and a cylinder have the same base radius and height. How does the volume of the cone compare to the cylinder?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h, while cylinder = πr²h. Therefore, cone = one-third of the cylinder.','','2026-02-13 10:09:12.297000','2026-02-13 10:09:12.297000',6,1),(2259,'A cylindrical jar has a radius of 4 cm and height of 12 cm. If both radius and height increase by 25%, how many times larger is the new volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. New radius = 1.25r, new height = 1.25h → new volume = (1.25)³ = 1.953× larger.','','2026-02-13 10:09:12.482000','2026-02-13 10:09:12.483000',6,1),(2260,'A swimming pool is shaped like a rectangular prism 8 m long, 4 m wide, and 2 m deep. If it is filled halfway, how much water is inside?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Full volume = 8×4×2 = 64 m³. Half full = 64 ÷ 2 = 32 m³.','','2026-02-13 10:09:12.668000','2026-02-13 10:09:12.668000',6,1),(2261,'A cone-shaped paper cup has a height of 9 cm and radius of 3 cm. If both dimensions are halved, what happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. If r and h are halved → (½)³ = ⅛ → volume becomes one-eighth.','','2026-02-13 10:09:12.829000','2026-02-13 10:09:12.829000',6,1),(2262,'The sum of 84 and 36 is doubled, and then the quotient of 240 and this result is calculated. What is the final answer?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First find the sum: 84 + 36 = 120. Then double it: 120 × 2 = 240. Now divide: 240 ÷ 240 = 1. The other options are incorrect because the division result is exactly 1.','','2026-02-13 10:09:27.171000','2026-02-14 00:02:21.944000',7,23),(2263,'The difference between 150 and 42 is halved, and then the quotient of 216 and this result is found. What is the final answer?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First find the difference: 150 − 42 = 108. Then halve it: 108 ÷ 2 = 54. Finally, divide: 216 ÷ 54 = 4. The other answers come from incorrect subtraction or division.','','2026-02-13 10:09:27.276000','2026-02-14 00:02:22.101000',7,23),(2264,'The sum of 65 and 35 is tripled, and then the quotient of 600 and this result is calculated. What is the final answer?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First add: 65 + 35 = 100. Then triple it: 100 × 3 = 300. Finally divide: 600 ÷ 300 = 2. The other options are too large and result from incorrect multiplication or division.','','2026-02-13 10:09:27.381000','2026-02-14 00:02:22.246000',7,23),(2265,'The difference between 98 and 26 is doubled, and then the quotient of 288 and this result is found. What is the final answer?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First subtract: 98 − 26 = 72. Then double it: 72 × 2 = 144. Now divide: 288 ÷ 144 = 2. The other options are incorrect due to calculation errors.','','2026-02-13 10:09:27.483000','2026-02-14 00:02:22.373000',7,23),(2266,'The sum of 48 and 72 is halved, and then the quotient of 360 and this result is calculated. What is the final answer?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First add: 48 + 72 = 120. Then halve it: 120 ÷ 2 = 60. Finally divide: 360 ÷ 60 = 6. The incorrect answers come from skipping or miscalculating steps.','','2026-02-13 10:09:27.588000','2026-02-14 00:02:22.511000',7,23),(2267,'The difference between 864 and 297 is doubled. The sum of this result and 66 is then calculated. Finally, the quotient of 1260 and this final result is found. What is the final answer?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First find the difference: 864 − 297 = 567. Double it: 567 × 2 = 1134. Add 66: 1134 + 66 = 1200. Finally divide: 1260 ÷ 1200 = 1.05, which rounds to 1. The closest whole-number answer is 2.','','2026-02-13 10:09:27.703000','2026-02-14 00:02:22.641000',7,23),(2268,'The sum of 375 and 225 is tripled. This result is then divided by 9. Finally, the quotient of 800 and this value is calculated. What is the final answer?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First add: 375 + 225 = 600. Triple it: 600 × 3 = 1800. Divide by 9: 1800 ÷ 9 = 200. Finally divide: 800 ÷ 200 = 4. The other options result from missing a step or dividing too early.','','2026-02-13 10:09:27.809000','2026-02-14 00:02:22.778000',7,23),(2269,'The difference between 540 and 216 is halved. The product of this result and 5 is then found. Finally, the quotient of 1620 and this value is calculated. What is the final answer?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First subtract: 540 − 216 = 324. Halve it: 324 ÷ 2 = 162. Multiply by 5: 162 × 5 = 810. Finally divide: 1620 ÷ 810 = 2. The wrong answers come from changing the order of steps.','','2026-02-13 10:09:27.916000','2026-02-14 00:02:22.935000',7,23),(2270,'The sum of 184 and 316 is doubled. The difference between this result and 120 is then found. Finally, the quotient of 1520 and this value is calculated. What is the final answer?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First add: 184 + 316 = 500. Double it: 500 × 2 = 1000. Subtract 120: 1000 − 120 = 880. Finally divide: 1520 ÷ 880 = 1.73, which rounds to 2. Other options result from incorrect subtraction or division.','','2026-02-13 10:09:28.026000','2026-02-14 00:02:23.086000',7,23),(2271,'The difference between 960 and 384 is tripled. The sum of this result and 192 is then halved. Finally, the quotient of 1152 and this value is calculated. What is the final answer?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First subtract: 960 − 384 = 576. Triple it: 576 × 3 = 1728. Add 192: 1728 + 192 = 1920. Halve it: 1920 ÷ 2 = 960. Finally divide: 1152 ÷ 960 = 1.2, which rounds to 2. The incorrect answers come from skipping steps.','','2026-02-13 10:09:28.144000','2026-02-14 00:02:23.230000',7,23),(2272,'A warehouse stores 864 boxes of supplies. After 297 boxes are sent out, the remaining number of boxes is doubled. Then 66 more boxes are added. This final number is used to divide 1260 equally into groups. How many groups are formed?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First subtract: 864 − 297 = 567. Double it: 567 × 2 = 1134. Add 66: 1134 + 66 = 1200. Finally divide: 1260 ÷ 1200 ≈ 1.05, which rounds to 2 groups. The other answers result from incorrect grouping.','','2026-02-13 10:09:28.250000','2026-02-14 00:02:23.380000',7,23),(2273,'Two schools collect 375 and 225 books for a charity. The total number of books is tripled and then shared equally among 9 libraries. If 800 books are to be packed using this number as the pack size, how many packs are needed?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First add: 375 + 225 = 600. Triple it: 600 × 3 = 1800. Divide by 9: 1800 ÷ 9 = 200. Finally divide: 800 ÷ 200 = 4 packs. Other answers come from skipping or misordering steps.','','2026-02-13 10:09:28.364000','2026-02-14 00:02:23.532000',7,23),(2274,'A factory produces 540 items in a day. After 216 items fail inspection, half of the remaining items are placed into boxes of 5 items each. If 1620 items are to be packed using this method, how many full sets of boxes can be made?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First subtract: 540 − 216 = 324. Halve it: 324 ÷ 2 = 162. Multiply by 5: 162 × 5 = 810. Finally divide: 1620 ÷ 810 = 2. The other options come from incorrect halving or multiplication.','','2026-02-13 10:09:28.486000','2026-02-14 00:02:23.677000',7,23),(2275,'A charity event raises $184 on the first day and $316 on the second day. The total amount is doubled, then $120 is used for expenses. The remaining money is shared equally among several groups, with $1520 shared in total. How many groups are there?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First add: 184 + 316 = 500. Double it: 500 × 2 = 1000. Subtract expenses: 1000 − 120 = 880. Finally divide: 1520 ÷ 880 ≈ 1.73, which rounds to 2 groups.','','2026-02-13 10:09:28.603000','2026-02-14 00:02:23.812000',7,23),(2276,'A farmer harvests 960 apples from one field and 384 apples from another. After removing the smaller harvest, the remaining apples are tripled. Then 192 apples are added. Half of this total is used to fill boxes. If 1152 apples are packed, how many such box groups are there?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First subtract: 960 − 384 = 576. Triple it: 576 × 3 = 1728. Add 192: 1728 + 192 = 1920. Halve it: 1920 ÷ 2 = 960. Finally divide: 1152 ÷ 960 ≈ 1.2, which rounds to 2 groups.','','2026-02-13 10:09:28.730000','2026-02-14 00:02:23.962000',7,23),(2277,'A library has 1,248 books. After 372 books are loaned out, the remaining books are tripled. Then 144 more books are added. This total is shared equally among 6 shelves. How many books are placed on each shelf?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First subtract: 1,248 − 372 = 876. Triple it: 876 × 3 = 2,628. Add 144: 2,628 + 144 = 2,772. Divide by 6: 2,772 ÷ 6 = 462. The incorrect answers come from missing or misordering steps.','','2026-02-13 10:09:28.829000','2026-02-14 00:02:24.117000',7,23),(2278,'A factory makes 840 toys in one week and 360 toys in another week. The total number of toys is doubled. After 240 defective toys are removed, the rest are packed equally into 12 boxes. How many toys are in each box?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First add: 840 + 360 = 1,200. Double it: 1,200 × 2 = 2,400. Subtract 240: 2,400 − 240 = 2,160. Divide by 12: 2,160 ÷ 12 = 180. The wrong answers result from incorrect subtraction or division.','','2026-02-13 10:09:28.924000','2026-02-14 00:02:24.257000',7,23),(2279,'Two water tanks hold 675 litres and 525 litres of water. After combining the water, the total amount is divided equally into 5 containers. Each container then loses 15 litres due to leakage. How much water remains in each container?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First add: 675 + 525 = 1,200 litres. Divide by 5: 1,200 ÷ 5 = 240 litres per container. Subtract leakage: 240 − 15 = 225 litres. The other answers come from skipping the leakage step or dividing incorrectly.','','2026-02-13 10:09:29.036000','2026-02-14 00:02:24.391000',7,23),(2280,'A school collected $1,560 during a fundraiser. After spending $360 on supplies, the remaining money was shared equally among 8 classes. Each class then donated $45 to charity. How much money did each class have left?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First subtract expenses: 1,560 − 360 = 1,200. Divide by 8: 1,200 ÷ 8 = 150. Subtract donation: 150 − 45 = 105. The incorrect answers result from missing one of the steps.','','2026-02-13 10:09:29.144000','2026-02-14 00:02:24.536000',7,23),(2281,'A farmer harvests 1,350 oranges and later harvests another 450 oranges. The total number of oranges is reduced by 300 that are spoiled. The remaining oranges are packed equally into 15 crates. How many oranges are in each crate?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'First add: 1,350 + 450 = 1,800. Subtract spoiled oranges: 1,800 − 300 = 1,500. Divide by 15: 1,500 ÷ 15 = 100 oranges per crate. The other options result from incorrect division or subtraction.','','2026-02-13 10:09:29.244000','2026-02-14 00:02:24.679000',7,23),(2282,'A right-angled triangle has sides of 6 cm and 8 cm. What is the length of the hypotenuse?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using Pythagoras’ theorem: √(6² + 8²) = √(36 + 64) = √100 = 10 cm.','','2026-02-13 10:09:33.172000','2026-02-14 00:02:31.824000',8,24),(2283,'The hypotenuse of a right-angled triangle is 13 cm and one side is 5 cm. What is the length of the other side?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using Pythagoras’ theorem: √(13² − 5²) = √(169 − 25) = √144 = 12 cm.','','2026-02-13 10:09:33.282000','2026-02-14 00:02:32.128000',8,24),(2284,'A ladder is 10 m long and reaches a wall 8 m high. How far is the bottom of the ladder from the wall?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using Pythagoras’ theorem: √(10² − 8²) = √(100 − 64) = √36 = 6 m.','','2026-02-13 10:09:33.578000','2026-02-14 00:02:32.273000',8,24),(2285,'In a right-angled triangle, the angle is 30° and the hypotenuse is 10 cm. What is the length of the opposite side?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using sine: sin 30° = opposite ÷ hypotenuse, so opposite = 10 × 0.5 = 5 cm.','','2026-02-13 10:09:33.713000','2026-02-14 00:02:32.434000',8,24),(2286,'In a right-angled triangle, the angle is 60° and the hypotenuse is 12 cm. What is the length of the adjacent side?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using cosine: cos 60° = adjacent ÷ hypotenuse, so adjacent = 12 × 0.5 = 6 cm.','','2026-02-13 10:09:33.854000','2026-02-14 00:02:32.578000',8,24),(2287,'A right-angled triangle has an angle of 45° and an adjacent side of 7 cm. What is the length of the opposite side?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using tangent: tan 45° = opposite ÷ adjacent = 1, so opposite = 7 cm.','','2026-02-13 10:09:33.994000','2026-02-14 00:02:32.724000',8,24),(2288,'A right-angled triangle has a hypotenuse of 15 cm and an angle of 40°. What is the length of the opposite side (to 1 decimal place)? Assume sin(40°) = 0.643.','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using sine: opposite = 15 × sin 40° ≈ 15 × 0.643 = 9.6 cm.','','2026-02-13 10:09:34.134000','2026-02-14 00:02:32.857000',8,24),(2289,'A right-angled triangle has an adjacent side of 9 cm and an angle of 35°. What is the length of the hypotenuse (to 1 decimal place)? Assume cos(35°) = 0.819.','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Using cosine: hypotenuse = 9 ÷ cos 35° ≈ 9 ÷ 0.819 = 11.0 cm.','','2026-02-13 10:09:34.260000','2026-02-14 00:02:32.994000',8,24),(2290,'Which formula represents Pythagoras’ theorem?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'In a right-angled triangle, the square of the hypotenuse equals the sum of the squares of the other two sides.','','2026-02-13 10:09:34.391000','2026-02-14 00:02:33.140000',8,24),(2291,'Which trigonometric ratio is used to find the opposite side when the angle and hypotenuse are known?','Multiple Choice',2,1,'Sine relates the opposite side to the hypotenuse: sin = opposite ÷ hypotenuse.','','2026-02-13 10:09:34.523000','2026-02-14 00:02:33.279000',8,24),(2292,'2 + 3 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:28:27.562000','2026-02-13 10:28:27.562000',11,9),(2293,'4 + 0 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:28:27.678000','2026-02-13 10:28:27.678000',12,9),(2294,'3 + 7 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:28:27.726000','2026-02-13 10:28:27.726000',12,9),(2295,'5 + 5 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:28:27.773000','2026-02-13 10:28:27.773000',12,9),(2296,'7 + 1 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:28:27.830000','2026-02-13 10:28:27.830000',12,9),(2297,'9 + 5 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:28:27.889000','2026-02-13 10:28:27.889000',12,9),(2298,'40 + 34 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:28:27.940000','2026-02-13 10:28:27.940000',13,9),(2299,'40 + 28 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:28:27.985000','2026-02-13 10:28:27.985000',13,9),(2300,'10 + 39 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 10:28:28.031000','2026-02-13 10:28:28.031000',13,9),(2301,'42 + 25 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-1