ncrease in the surface area of the cube?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the original side length of the cube = x, Original surface area = 6𝑥². New side length = 1.5𝑥, New surface area = 6(1.5𝑥)² = 13.5𝑥². Percentage increase = (New surface area - Original surface area) / Original surface area * 100% = (13.5𝑥² - 6𝑥²) / 6𝑥² * 100% = 125%.','','2026-02-13 10:28:45.530000','2026-02-13 10:28:45.530000',6,1),(2445,'The sides of a square are doubled. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the side = x, original area = x². New side = 2x, new area = (2x)² = 4x². Percentage increase = (4x² - x²) / x² × 100 = 300%.','','2026-02-13 10:28:45.688000','2026-02-13 10:28:45.688000',6,1),(2446,'The radius of a circle increases by 20%. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². If radius increases by 20%, new radius = 1.2r. New area = (1.2r)² = 1.44r², meaning a 44% increase.','','2026-02-13 10:28:45.838000','2026-02-13 10:28:45.838000',6,1),(2447,'The height of a cylinder is doubled and the radius is halved. What happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume = πr²h. New volume = π(½r)²(2h) = πr²h. The volume remains unchanged.','','2026-02-13 10:28:46.004000','2026-02-13 10:28:46.004000',6,1),(2448,'The length of a rectangle is increased by 50%, and the width stays the same. What is the percentage increase in area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area = L × W. Increasing length by 50% makes it 1.5L, so new area = 1.5LW. Increase = 50%.','','2026-02-13 10:28:46.154000','2026-02-13 10:28:46.154000',6,1),(2449,'A cube’s edge length is tripled. By what factor does its volume increase?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. If side is tripled, volume increases by 3³ = 27 times.','','2026-02-13 10:28:46.316000','2026-02-13 10:28:46.316000',6,1),(2450,'All dimensions of a rectangular prism are reduced by 50%. What is the percentage decrease in its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ length × width × height. If each is halved, new volume = (0.5)³ = 0.125, meaning 12.5% remains, so an 87.5% decrease.','','2026-02-13 10:28:46.489000','2026-02-13 10:28:46.489000',6,1),(2451,'The diameter of a circle is reduced by 40%. What is the percentage decrease in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². New radius = 0.6r, new area = 0.36r² → area decreases by 64%.','','2026-02-13 10:28:46.645000','2026-02-13 10:28:46.645000',6,1),(2452,'The volume of a cube doubles. What is the percentage increase in the cube’s side length?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = ³√2 × old side ≈ 1.26×, which is a 26% increase.','','2026-02-13 10:28:46.801000','2026-02-13 10:28:46.801000',6,1),(2453,'A rectangle’s perimeter is 60 cm. If both its length and width increase by 25%, what is the new perimeter?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Perimeter ∝ (L + W). If both increase by 25%, total perimeter increases by 25% → 60 × 1.25 = 75 cm.','','2026-02-13 10:28:46.963000','2026-02-13 10:28:46.964000',6,1),(2454,'The surface area of a cube is 150 cm². If the edge length doubles, what is the new surface area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Surface area ∝ side². Doubling the side makes the area 4 times larger → 150 × 4 = 600 cm².','','2026-02-13 10:28:47.111000','2026-02-13 10:28:47.111000',6,1),(2455,'A cube-shaped gift box has a side length of 10 cm. If the side is increased by 20%, what is the new volume of the box compared to the old one?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = 1.2× old side, so new volume = (1.2)³ = 1.728× the original.','','2026-02-13 10:28:47.281000','2026-02-13 10:28:47.281000',6,1),(2456,'A rectangular water tank is 2 m long, 1.5 m wide, and 1 m high. If the height is doubled, how much more water can it hold?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles the capacity → 2× the amount of water.','','2026-02-13 10:28:47.453000','2026-02-13 10:28:47.453000',6,1),(2457,'A cylindrical candle has a radius of 5 cm and height of 10 cm. If the radius is doubled and height stays the same, how many times greater is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cylinder = πr²h. Doubling radius makes r² → (2r)² = 4r² → volume increases 4 times.','','2026-02-13 10:28:47.614000','2026-02-13 10:28:47.614000',6,1),(2458,'A cone has a radius of 3 cm and height of 8 cm. If both radius and height are doubled, how many times greater is the volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h. If both r and h double → (2r)²(2h) = 8× bigger.','','2026-02-13 10:28:47.770000','2026-02-13 10:28:47.770000',6,1),(2459,'A cylindrical water bottle has a volume of 500 mL. If its height is doubled but the radius stays the same, what will the new volume be?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles volume → 500 mL × 2 = 1 L.','','2026-02-13 10:28:47.923000','2026-02-13 10:28:47.923000',6,1),(2460,'A metal cube is melted and reshaped into a cylinder with the same volume. If the cube’s side is 6 cm, what is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cube = side³ = 6³ = 216 cm³.','','2026-02-13 10:28:48.074000','2026-02-13 10:28:48.074000',6,1),(2461,'A cone and a cylinder have the same base radius and height. How does the volume of the cone compare to the cylinder?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h, while cylinder = πr²h. Therefore, cone = one-third of the cylinder.','','2026-02-13 10:28:48.232000','2026-02-13 10:28:48.232000',6,1),(2462,'A cylindrical jar has a radius of 4 cm and height of 12 cm. If both radius and height increase by 25%, how many times larger is the new volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. New radius = 1.25r, new height = 1.25h → new volume = (1.25)³ = 1.953× larger.','','2026-02-13 10:28:48.390000','2026-02-13 10:28:48.390000',6,1),(2463,'A swimming pool is shaped like a rectangular prism 8 m long, 4 m wide, and 2 m deep. If it is filled halfway, how much water is inside?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Full volume = 8×4×2 = 64 m³. Half full = 64 ÷ 2 = 32 m³.','','2026-02-13 10:28:48.556000','2026-02-13 10:28:48.556000',6,1),(2464,'A cone-shaped paper cup has a height of 9 cm and radius of 3 cm. If both dimensions are halved, what happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. If r and h are halved → (½)³ = ⅛ → volume becomes one-eighth.','','2026-02-13 10:28:48.708000','2026-02-13 10:28:48.709000',6,1),(2465,'1 + 2 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:07:22.337000','2026-02-13 11:07:22.337000',12,9),(2466,'6 + 4 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:07:22.414000','2026-02-13 11:07:22.414000',12,9),(2467,'4 + 3 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:07:22.487000','2026-02-13 11:07:22.487000',12,9),(2468,'21 + 44 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:07:22.552000','2026-02-13 11:07:22.552000',13,9),(2469,'13 + 15 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:07:22.614000','2026-02-13 11:07:22.614000',13,9),(2470,'30 + 27 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:07:22.672000','2026-02-13 11:07:22.672000',13,9),(2471,'30 + 29 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:07:22.725000','2026-02-13 11:07:22.725000',13,9),(2472,'22 + 10 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:07:22.779000','2026-02-13 11:07:22.779000',13,9),(2473,'30 + 20 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:07:22.834000','2026-02-13 11:07:22.834000',13,9),(2474,'42 + 31 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:07:22.887000','2026-02-13 11:07:22.887000',13,9),(2475,'43 + 14 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:07:22.943000','2026-02-13 11:07:22.943000',13,9),(2476,'16 + 39 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:07:23.003000','2026-02-13 11:07:23.003000',14,9),(2477,'22 + 28 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:07:23.051000','2026-02-13 11:07:23.051000',14,9),(2478,'47 + 17 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:07:23.095000','2026-02-13 11:07:23.095000',14,9),(2479,'53 + 58 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:07:23.142000','2026-02-13 11:07:23.142000',14,9),(2480,'59 + 46 = ?','short_answer',1,