,(2617,'There are 45 stickers shared equally among 9 students. How many stickers does each student get?','Multiple Choice',1,1,'45 ÷ 9 = 5. Each student gets 5 stickers.','','2026-02-13 11:07:39.486000','2026-02-14 00:01:59.044000',4,23),(2618,'A box has 48 crayons divided equally into 6 packs. How many crayons are in each pack?','Multiple Choice',1,1,'48 ÷ 6 = 8. Each pack has 8 crayons.','','2026-02-13 11:07:39.610000','2026-02-14 00:01:59.210000',4,23),(2619,'There are 56 oranges shared equally among 7 baskets. How many oranges are in each basket?','Multiple Choice',1,1,'56 ÷ 7 = 8. Each basket has 8 oranges.','','2026-02-13 11:07:39.725000','2026-02-14 00:01:59.355000',4,23),(2620,'A teacher arranges 36 chairs into 4 equal rows. How many chairs are in each row?','Multiple Choice',1,1,'36 ÷ 4 = 9. Each row has 9 chairs.','','2026-02-13 11:07:39.841000','2026-02-14 00:01:59.504000',4,23),(2621,'24 muffins are shared equally among 3 plates. How many muffins are on each plate?','Multiple Choice',1,1,'24 ÷ 3 = 8. Each plate has 8 muffins.','','2026-02-13 11:07:39.960000','2026-02-14 00:01:59.674000',4,23),(2622,'There are 63 beads divided equally into 9 strings. How many beads are on each string?','Multiple Choice',1,1,'63 ÷ 9 = 7. Each string has 7 beads.','','2026-02-13 11:07:40.089000','2026-02-14 00:01:59.837000',4,23),(2623,'A farmer puts 50 eggs equally into 10 boxes. How many eggs are in each box?','Multiple Choice',1,1,'50 ÷ 10 = 5. Each box has 5 eggs.','','2026-02-13 11:07:40.215000','2026-02-14 00:02:00.005000',4,23),(2624,'There are 72 marbles shared equally among 8 children. How many marbles does each child get?','Multiple Choice',1,1,'72 ÷ 8 = 9. Each child gets 9 marbles.','','2026-02-13 11:07:40.343000','2026-02-14 00:02:00.167000',4,23),(2625,'Calculate the area of this shape.','multiple_choice',1,1,'Calculate the area using πr².','questions/year6/measurements/image9.png','2026-02-13 11:07:43.126000','2026-02-13 11:07:43.155000',6,1),(2626,'The width of a cube increases by 50%, but it remains a cube. What is the percentage increase in the surface area of the cube?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the original side length of the cube = x, Original surface area = 6𝑥². New side length = 1.5𝑥, New surface area = 6(1.5𝑥)² = 13.5𝑥². Percentage increase = (New surface area - Original surface area) / Original surface area * 100% = (13.5𝑥² - 6𝑥²) / 6𝑥² * 100% = 125%.','','2026-02-13 11:07:43.670000','2026-02-13 11:07:43.670000',6,1),(2627,'The sides of a square are doubled. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the side = x, original area = x². New side = 2x, new area = (2x)² = 4x². Percentage increase = (4x² - x²) / x² × 100 = 300%.','','2026-02-13 11:07:43.939000','2026-02-13 11:07:43.939000',6,1),(2628,'The radius of a circle increases by 20%. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². If radius increases by 20%, new radius = 1.2r. New area = (1.2r)² = 1.44r², meaning a 44% increase.','','2026-02-13 11:07:44.143000','2026-02-13 11:07:44.143000',6,1),(2629,'The height of a cylinder is doubled and the radius is halved. What happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume = πr²h. New volume = π(½r)²(2h) = πr²h. The volume remains unchanged.','','2026-02-13 11:07:44.408000','2026-02-13 11:07:44.408000',6,1),(2630,'The length of a rectangle is increased by 50%, and the width stays the same. What is the percentage increase in area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area = L × W. Increasing length by 50% makes it 1.5L, so new area = 1.5LW. Increase = 50%.','','2026-02-13 11:07:44.603000','2026-02-13 11:07:44.603000',6,1),(2631,'A cube’s edge length is tripled. By what factor does its volume increase?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. If side is tripled, volume increases by 3³ = 27 times.','','2026-02-13 11:07:44.860000','2026-02-13 11:07:44.860000',6,1),(2632,'All dimensions of a rectangular prism are reduced by 50%. What is the percentage decrease in its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ length × width × height. If each is halved, new volume = (0.5)³ = 0.125, meaning 12.5% remains, so an 87.5% decrease.','','2026-02-13 11:07:45.079000','2026-02-13 11:07:45.079000',6,1),(2633,'The diameter of a circle is reduced by 40%. What is the percentage decrease in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². New radius = 0.6r, new area = 0.36r² → area decreases by 64%.','','2026-02-13 11:07:45.304000','2026-02-13 11:07:45.304000',6,1),(2634,'The volume of a cube doubles. What is the percentage increase in the cube’s side length?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = ³√2 × old side ≈ 1.26×, which is a 26% increase.','','2026-02-13 11:07:45.578000','2026-02-13 11:07:45.578000',6,1),(2635,'A rectangle’s perimeter is 60 cm. If both its length and width increase by 25%, what is the new perimeter?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Perimeter ∝ (L + W). If both increase by 25%, total perimeter increases by 25% → 60 × 1.25 = 75 cm.','','2026-02-13 11:07:45.757000','2026-02-13 11:07:45.757000',6,1),(2636,'The surface area of a cube is 150 cm². If the edge length doubles, what is the new surface area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Surface area ∝ side². Doubling the side makes the area 4 times larger → 150 × 4 = 600 cm².','','2026-02-13 11:07:45.983000','2026-02-13 11:07:45.983000',6,1),(2637,'A cube-shaped gift box has a side length of 10 cm. If the side is increased by 20%, what is the new volume of the box compared to the old one?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = 1.2× old side, so new volume = (1.2)³ = 1.728× the original.','','2026-02-13 11:07:46.202000','2026-02-13 11:07:46.202000',6,1),(2638,'A rectangular water tank is 2 m long, 1.5 m wide, and 1 m high. If the height is doubled, how much more water can it hold?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles the capacity → 2× the amount of water.','','2026-02-13 11:07:46.405000','2026-02-13 11:07:46.405000',6,1),(2639,'A cylindrical candle has a radius of 5 cm and height of 10 cm. If the radius is doubled and height stays the same, how many times greater is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cylinder = πr²h. Doubling radius makes r² → (2r)² = 4r² → volume increases 4 times.','','2026-02-13 11:07:46.600000','2026-02-13 11:07:46.600000',6,1),(2640,'A cone has a radius of 3 cm and height of 8 cm. If both radius and height are doubled, how many times greater is the volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h. If both r and h double → (2r)²(2h) = 8× bigger.','','2026-02-13 11:07:46.804000','2026-02-13 11:07:46.804000',6,1),(2641,'A cylindrical water bottle has a volume of 500 mL. If its height is doubled but the radius stays the same, what will the new volume be?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles volume → 500 mL × 2 = 1 L.','','2026-02-13 11:07:47.013000','2026-02-13 11:07:47.013000',6,1),(2642,'A metal cube is melted and reshaped into a cylinder with the same volume. If the cube’s side is 6 cm, what is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cube = side³ = 6³ = 216 cm³.','','2026-02-13 11:07:47.240000','2026-02-13 11:07:47.240000',6,1),(2643,'A cone and a cylinder have the same base radius and height. How does the volume of the cone compare to the cylinder?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h, while cylinder = πr²h. Therefore, cone = one-third of the cylinder.','','2026-02-13 11:07:47.451000','2026-02-13 11:07:47.451000',6,1),(2644,'A cylindrical jar has a radius of 4 cm and height of 12 cm. If both radius and height increase by 25%, how many times larger is the new volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. New radius = 1.25r, new height = 1.25h → new volume = (1.25)³ = 1.953× larger.','','2026-02-13 11:07:47.650000','2026-02-13 11:07:47.650000',6,1),(2645,'A swimming pool is shaped like a rectangular prism 8 m long, 4 m wide, and 2 m deep. If it is filled halfway, how much water is inside?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Full volume = 8×4×2 = 64 m³. Half full = 64 ÷ 2 = 32 m³.','','2026-02-13 11:07:47.855000','2026-02-13 11:07:47.855000',6,1),(2646,'A cone-shaped paper cup has a height of 9 cm and radius of 3 cm. If both dimensions are halved, what happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. If r and h are halved → (½)³ = ⅛ → volume becomes one-eighth.','','2026-02-13 11:07:48.047000','2026-02-13 11:07:48.047000',6,1),(2647,'7 + 9 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:19:12.251000','2026-02-13 11:19:12.251000',12,9),(2648,'1 + 9 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:19:16.319000','2026-02-13 11:19:16.319000',12,9),(2649,'0 + 0 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:19:16.492000','2026-02-13 11:19:16.492000',12,9),(2650,'3 + 8 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:19:26.399000','2026-02-13 11:19:26.399000',12,9),(2651,'14 + 10 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:19:26.548000','2026-02-13 11:19:26.548000',13,9),(2652,'22 + 40 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:19:26.620000','2026-02-13 11:19:26.620000',13,9),(2653,'41 + 10 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:19:26.801000','2026-02-13 11:19:26.801000',13,9),(2654,'33 + 44 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:19:26.901000','2026-02-13 11:19:26.901000',13,9),(2655,'33 + 35 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:19:26.980000','2026-02-13 11:19:26.980000',13,9),(2656,'34 + 35 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:19:27.041000','2026-02-13 11:19:27.041000',13,9),(2657,'42 + 43 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:19:27.101000','2026-02-13 11:19:27.101000',13,9),(2658,'32 + 45 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:19:27.179000','2026-02-13 11:19:27.179000',13,9),(2659,'23 + 31 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:19:27.244000','2026-02-13 11:19:27.244000',13,9),(2660,'32 + 68 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:19:27.312000','2026-02-13 11:19:27.312000',14,9),(2661,'65 + 88 = ?','short_answer',1,1,'','','2026-02-13 11:19:27.378000