n the surface area of the cube?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the original side length of the cube = x, Original surface area = 6𝑥². New side length = 1.5𝑥, New surface area = 6(1.5𝑥)² = 13.5𝑥². Percentage increase = (New surface area - Original surface area) / Original surface area * 100% = (13.5𝑥² - 6𝑥²) / 6𝑥² * 100% = 125%.','','2026-02-14 00:02:03.505000','2026-02-14 00:02:03.505000',6,1),(2910,'The sides of a square are doubled. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the side = x, original area = x². New side = 2x, new area = (2x)² = 4x². Percentage increase = (4x² - x²) / x² × 100 = 300%.','','2026-02-14 00:02:03.689000','2026-02-14 00:02:03.689000',6,1),(2911,'The radius of a circle increases by 20%. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². If radius increases by 20%, new radius = 1.2r. New area = (1.2r)² = 1.44r², meaning a 44% increase.','','2026-02-14 00:02:03.878000','2026-02-14 00:02:03.878000',6,1),(2912,'The height of a cylinder is doubled and the radius is halved. What happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume = πr²h. New volume = π(½r)²(2h) = πr²h. The volume remains unchanged.','','2026-02-14 00:02:04.070000','2026-02-14 00:02:04.070000',6,1),(2913,'The length of a rectangle is increased by 50%, and the width stays the same. What is the percentage increase in area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area = L × W. Increasing length by 50% makes it 1.5L, so new area = 1.5LW. Increase = 50%.','','2026-02-14 00:02:04.257000','2026-02-14 00:02:04.257000',6,1),(2914,'A cube’s edge length is tripled. By what factor does its volume increase?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. If side is tripled, volume increases by 3³ = 27 times.','','2026-02-14 00:02:04.437000','2026-02-14 00:02:04.437000',6,1),(2915,'All dimensions of a rectangular prism are reduced by 50%. What is the percentage decrease in its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ length × width × height. If each is halved, new volume = (0.5)³ = 0.125, meaning 12.5% remains, so an 87.5% decrease.','','2026-02-14 00:02:04.637000','2026-02-14 00:02:04.637000',6,1),(2916,'The diameter of a circle is reduced by 40%. What is the percentage decrease in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². New radius = 0.6r, new area = 0.36r² → area decreases by 64%.','','2026-02-14 00:02:04.827000','2026-02-14 00:02:04.827000',6,1),(2917,'The volume of a cube doubles. What is the percentage increase in the cube’s side length?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = ³√2 × old side ≈ 1.26×, which is a 26% increase.','','2026-02-14 00:02:05.007000','2026-02-14 00:02:05.007000',6,1),(2918,'A rectangle’s perimeter is 60 cm. If both its length and width increase by 25%, what is the new perimeter?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Perimeter ∝ (L + W). If both increase by 25%, total perimeter increases by 25% → 60 × 1.25 = 75 cm.','','2026-02-14 00:02:05.176000','2026-02-14 00:02:05.176000',6,1),(2919,'The surface area of a cube is 150 cm². If the edge length doubles, what is the new surface area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Surface area ∝ side². Doubling the side makes the area 4 times larger → 150 × 4 = 600 cm².','','2026-02-14 00:02:05.343000','2026-02-14 00:02:05.343000',6,1),(2920,'A cube-shaped gift box has a side length of 10 cm. If the side is increased by 20%, what is the new volume of the box compared to the old one?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = 1.2× old side, so new volume = (1.2)³ = 1.728× the original.','','2026-02-14 00:02:05.504000','2026-02-14 00:02:05.504000',6,1),(2921,'A rectangular water tank is 2 m long, 1.5 m wide, and 1 m high. If the height is doubled, how much more water can it hold?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles the capacity → 2× the amount of water.','','2026-02-14 00:02:05.663000','2026-02-14 00:02:05.663000',6,1),(2922,'A cylindrical candle has a radius of 5 cm and height of 10 cm. If the radius is doubled and height stays the same, how many times greater is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cylinder = πr²h. Doubling radius makes r² → (2r)² = 4r² → volume increases 4 times.','','2026-02-14 00:02:05.842000','2026-02-14 00:02:05.842000',6,1),(2923,'A cone has a radius of 3 cm and height of 8 cm. If both radius and height are doubled, how many times greater is the volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h. If both r and h double → (2r)²(2h) = 8× bigger.','','2026-02-14 00:02:06.019000','2026-02-14 00:02:06.019000',6,1),(2924,'A cylindrical water bottle has a volume of 500 mL. If its height is doubled but the radius stays the same, what will the new volume be?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles volume → 500 mL × 2 = 1 L.','','2026-02-14 00:02:06.185000','2026-02-14 00:02:06.185000',6,1),(2925,'A metal cube is melted and reshaped into a cylinder with the same volume. If the cube’s side is 6 cm, what is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cube = side³ = 6³ = 216 cm³.','','2026-02-14 00:02:06.340000','2026-02-14 00:02:06.340000',6,1),(2926,'A cone and a cylinder have the same base radius and height. How does the volume of the cone compare to the cylinder?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h, while cylinder = πr²h. Therefore, cone = one-third of the cylinder.','','2026-02-14 00:02:06.490000','2026-02-14 00:02:06.490000',6,1),(2927,'A cylindrical jar has a radius of 4 cm and height of 12 cm. If both radius and height increase by 25%, how many times larger is the new volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. New radius = 1.25r, new height = 1.25h → new volume = (1.25)³ = 1.953× larger.','','2026-02-14 00:02:06.648000','2026-02-14 00:02:06.648000',6,1),(2928,'A swimming pool is shaped like a rectangular prism 8 m long, 4 m wide, and 2 m deep. If it is filled halfway, how much water is inside?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Full volume = 8×4×2 = 64 m³. Half full = 64 ÷ 2 = 32 m³.','','2026-02-14 00:02:06.823000','2026-02-14 00:02:06.823000',6,1),(2929,'A cone-shaped paper cup has a height of 9 cm and radius of 3 cm. If both dimensions are halved, what happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. If r and h are halved → (½)³ = ⅛ → volume becomes one-eighth.','','2026-02-14 00:02:06.985000','2026-02-14 00:02:06.985000',6,1),(2930,'What is the prime factorisation of 84?','multiple_choice',1,1,'84 = 2 × 2 × 3 × 7.','','2026-02-17 03:23:26.827474','2026-02-17 03:23:26.827519',7,21),(2931,'What is the prime factorisation of 90?','multiple_choice',1,1,'90 = 2 × 3 × 3 × 5.','','2026-02-17 03:23:26.863669','2026-02-17 03:23:26.863703',7,21),(2932,'What is the LCM of 12 and 15?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Multiples of 12 and 15 meet at 60.','','2026-02-17 03:23:26.886925','2026-02-17 03:23:26.886977',7,21),(2933,'What is the LCM of 18 and 24?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Prime factor method gives LCM = 72.','','2026-02-17 03:23:26.910276','2026-02-17 03:23:26.910329',7,21),(2934,'What is the LCM of 6, 8 and 12?','multiple_choice',1,1,'LCM of 6, 8 and 12 is 24.','','2026-02-17 03:23:26.937713','2026-02-17 03:23:26.937792',7,21),(2935,'What is the HCF of 24 and 36?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Common factors: 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 12. Highest is 12.','','2026-02-17 03:23:26.960190','2026-02-17 03:23:26.960237',7,21),(2936,'What is the HCF of 45 and 75?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Prime factors give HCF = 15.','','2026-02-17 03:23:27.025149','2026-02-17 03:23:27.025185',7,21),(2937,'What is the HCF of 36, 54 and 90?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Common prime factors give HCF = 18.','','2026-02-17 03:23:27.046553','2026-02-17 03:23:27.046588',7,21),(2938,'Three bells ring every 8, 12 and 20 minutes. After how many minutes will they ring together?','multiple_choice',1,1,'LCM of 8, 12 and 20 is 120.','','2026-02-17 03:23:27.070337','2026-02-17 03:23:27.070391',7,21),(2939,'48 apples and 72 oranges are packed into identical boxes. What is the greatest number of boxes that can be made?','multiple_choice',1,1,'HCF of 48 and 72 is 24.','','2026-02-17 03:23:27.095452','2026-02-17 03:23:27.095506',7,21),(2940,'Factorise: x² + 5x + 6','multiple_choice',1,1,'Two numbers that multiply to 6 and add to 5 are 2 and 3.','','2026-02-20 20:29:22.914812','2026-02-20 20:29:22.914871',8,21),(2941,'Factorise: x² + 7x + 10','multiple_choice',1,1,'Two numbers that multiply to 10 and add to 7 are 5 and 2.','','2026-02-20 20:29:22.947376','2026-02-20 20:29:22.947402',8,21),(2942,'Factorise: x² + 9x + 20','multiple_choice',1,1,'4 and 5 multiply to 20 and add to 9.','','2026-02-20 20:29:22.968242','2026-02-20 20:29:22.968267',8,21),(2943,'Factorise: x² + 11x + 24','multiple_choice',1,1,'3 and 8 multiply to 24 and add to 11.','','2026-02-20 20:29:22.990005','2026-02-20 20:29:22.990030',8,21),(2944,'Factorise: x² - 5x + 6','multiple_choice',1,1,'Two numbers that multiply to 6 and add to -5 are -2 and -3.','','2026-02-20 20:29:23.012385','2026-02-20 20:29:23.012411',8,21),(2945,'Factorise: x² - 7x + 12','multiple_choice',1,1,'Two numbers that multiply to 12 and add to -7 are -3 and -4.','','2026-02-20 20:29:23.040253','2026-02-20 20:29:23.040278',8,21),(2946,'Factorise: x² + x - 6','multiple_choice',1,1,'3 and -2 multiply to -6 and add to 1.','','2026-02-20 20:29:23.061432','2026-02-20 20:29:23.061456',8,21),(2947,'Factorise: x² - 2x - 15','multiple_choice',1,1,'-5 and 3 multiply to -15 and add to -2.','','2026-02-20 20:29:23.083291','2026-02-20 20:29:23.083315',8,21),(2948,'Factorise: x² + 6x - 16','multiple_choice',1,1,'8 and -2 multiply to -16 and add to 6.','','2026-02-20 20:29:23.104120','2026-02-20 20:29:23.104144',8,21),(2949,'Factorise: x² - x - 12','multiple_choice',1,1,'-4 and 3 multiply to -12 and add to -1.','','2026-02-20 20:29:23.124274','2026-02-20 20:29:23.124297',8,21),(2950,'Today, Nina is working on her reading homework. She needs to read 3 pages. What fraction represents each page of the reading homework?','multiple_choice',1,1,'There are 3 equal pages to read. Each page is 1 out of 3 equal parts, which is 1/3.','','2026-02-21 01:17:50.790159','2026-02-21 01:17:50.790204',4,15),(2951,'Sam has to complete 4 math questions. What fraction of the work is one question?','multiple_choice',1,1,'There are 4 equal questions. One question is 1 out of 4 equal parts, which is 1/4.','','2026-02-21 01:17:50.851853','2026-02-21 01:17:50.851902',4,15),(2952,'Lily cut a sandwich into 2 equal pieces. What fraction is one piece?','multiple_choice',1,1,'The sandwich is divided into 2 equal parts. One part is 1/2.','','2026-02-21 01:17:50.897524','2026-02-21 01:17:50.897561',4,15),(2953,'A chocolate bar is divided into 5 equal pieces. What fraction is one piece?','multiple_choice',1,1,'There are 5 equal pieces. One piece is 1 out of 5, which is 1/5.','','2026-02-21 01:17:50.937773','2026-02-21 01:17:50.937809',4,15),(2954,'A pizza is cut into 8 equal slices. What fraction is one slice?','multiple_choice',1,1,'There are 8 equal slices. One slice is 1 out of 8, which is 1/8.','','2026-02-21 01:17:50.984127','2026-02-21 01:17:50.984163',4,15),(2955,'Tom needs to finish 6 spelling words. What fraction of the work is one word?','multiple_choice',1,1,'There are 6 equal words to complete. One word is 1 out of 6, which is 1/6.','','2026-02-21 01:17:51.030225','2026-02-21 01:17:51.030261',4,15),(2956,'There are 8 cars parked on Lola\'s street. 2 of the cars are red. What fraction of the cars are red?','multiple_choice',1,1,'2 out of 8 cars are red. So the fraction is 2/8. (This can also be simplified to 1/4.)','','2026-02-21 01:17:51.070126','2026-02-21 01:17:51.070162',4,15),(2957,'There are 10 apples in a basket. 3 of the apples are green. What fraction of the apples are green?','multiple_choice',1,1,'3 out of 10 apples are green. So the fraction is 3/10.','','2026-02-21 01:17:51.109159','2026-02-21 01:17:51.109195',4,15),(2958,'There are 6 students in a group. 4 are wearing hats. What fraction of the students are wearing hats?','multiple_choice',1,1,'4 out of 6 students are wearing hats. So the fraction is 4/6. (This can also be simplified to 2/3.)','','2026-02-21 01:17:51.146156','2026-02-21 01:17:51.146191',4,15),(2959,'There are 12 balloons at a party. 5 are blue. What fraction of the balloons are blue?','multiple_choice',1,1,'5 out of 12 balloons are blue. So the fraction is 5/12.','','2026-02-21 01:17:51.186114','2026-02-21 01:17:51.186149',4,15),(2960,'There are 9 books on a shelf. 3 are storybooks. What fraction of the books are storybooks?','multiple_choice',1,1,'3 out of 9 books are storybooks. So the fraction is 3/9. (This can also be simplified to 1/3.)','','2026-02-21 01:17:51.228691','2026-02-21 01:17:51.228725',4,15),(2961,'There are 9 people waiting for the train. One-third of them have an umbrella. How many people waiting for the train have an umbrella?','multiple_choice',1,1,'One-third means divide by 3. 9 ÷ 3 = 3. So 3 people have an umbrella.','','2026-02-21 01:17:51.270986','2026-02-21 01:17:51.271023',4,15),(2962,'There are 12 students in a class. One-fourth of them bring lunch from home. How many students bring lunch from home?','multiple_choice',1,1,'One-fourth means divide by 4. 12 ÷ 4 = 3. So 3 students bring lunch from home.','','2026-02-21 01:17:51.309535','2026-02-21 01:17:51.309571',4,15),(2963,'There are 15 cookies on a plate. One-third of them are chocolate. How many cookies are chocolate?','multiple_choice',1,1,'One-third means divide by 3. 15 ÷ 3 = 5. So 5 cookies are chocolate.','','2026-02-21 01:17:51.347661','2026-02-21 01:17:51.347696',4,15),(2964,'There are 8 balloons. One-half of them are red. How many balloons are red?','multiple_choice',1,1,'One-half means divide by 2. 8 ÷ 2 = 4. So 4 balloons are red.','','2026-02-21 01:17:51.385389','2026-02-21 01:17:51.385428',4,15),(2965,'There are 20 pencils in a box. One-fifth of them are new. How many pencils are new?','multiple_choice',1,1,'One-fifth means divide by 5. 20 ÷ 5 = 4. So 4 pencils are new.','','2026-02-21 01:17:51.422974','2026-02-21