4),(3004,'What is 300 + 20 + 6?','multiple_choice',1,1,'300 is 3 hundreds, 20 is 2 tens, and 6 is 6 ones. 300 + 20 + 6 = 326.','','2026-02-21 01:17:53.580434','2026-02-21 01:17:53.580466',4,14),(3005,'What is 700 + 80 + 9?','multiple_choice',1,1,'700 is 7 hundreds, 80 is 8 tens, and 9 is 9 ones. 700 + 80 + 9 = 789.','','2026-02-21 01:17:53.618850','2026-02-21 01:17:53.618882',4,14),(3006,'What is 400 + 0 + 5?','multiple_choice',1,1,'400 is 4 hundreds, 0 is 0 tens, and 5 is 5 ones. 400 + 0 + 5 = 405.','','2026-02-21 01:17:53.657266','2026-02-21 01:17:53.657297',4,14),(3007,'What number has 9 tens and 1 fewer one than tens?','multiple_choice',1,1,'9 tens = 90. 1 fewer one than 9 tens means 8 ones. 90 + 8 = 98.','','2026-02-21 01:17:53.694578','2026-02-21 01:17:53.694609',4,14),(3008,'What number has 6 tens and 2 more ones than tens?','multiple_choice',1,1,'6 tens = 60. 2 more ones than 6 means 8 ones. 60 + 8 = 68.','','2026-02-21 01:17:53.732153','2026-02-21 01:17:53.732186',4,14),(3009,'What number has 4 hundreds and 3 fewer tens than hundreds?','multiple_choice',1,1,'4 hundreds = 400. 3 fewer tens than 4 means 1 ten. 400 + 10 = 410.','','2026-02-21 01:17:53.770618','2026-02-21 01:17:53.770651',4,14),(3010,'What number has 7 tens and the same number of ones as tens?','multiple_choice',1,1,'7 tens = 70. The same number of ones as tens means 7 ones. 70 + 7 = 77.','','2026-02-21 01:17:53.806731','2026-02-21 01:17:53.806765',4,14),(3011,'What number has 8 hundreds and 2 more tens than hundreds?','multiple_choice',1,1,'8 hundreds = 800. 2 more tens than 8 means 10 tens (100). 800 + 100 = 900. But since the question asks for tens place only (8 + 2 = 10 tens = 100), the correct total becomes 900. (Correction: 800 + 100 = 900.)','','2026-02-21 01:17:53.845856','2026-02-21 01:17:53.845890',4,14),(3012,'Find the unknown length.','multiple_choice',1,1,'Use the given measurements to find the unknown length.','questions/year5/measurements/image1.png','2026-02-21 01:17:53.885834','2026-02-21 01:17:53.892581',5,1),(3013,'Find the unknown length.','multiple_choice',1,1,'Use the given measurements to find the unknown length.','questions/year5/measurements/image2.png','2026-02-21 01:17:53.936267','2026-02-21 01:17:53.941718',5,1),(3014,'Find the unknown length.','multiple_choice',1,1,'Use the given measurements to find the unknown length.','questions/year5/measurements/image3.png','2026-02-21 01:17:53.979876','2026-02-21 01:17:53.985928',5,1),(3015,'Find the unknown length.','multiple_choice',1,1,'Use the given measurements to find the unknown length.','questions/year5/measurements/image4.png','2026-02-21 01:17:54.027495','2026-02-21 01:17:54.032796',5,1),(3016,'Calculate the area of this shape.','multiple_choice',1,1,'Calculate the area using πr².','questions/year6/measurements/image9.png','2026-02-21 01:17:55.610675','2026-02-21 01:17:55.616459',6,1),(3017,'The width of a cube increases by 50%, but it remains a cube. What is the percentage increase in the surface area of the cube?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the original side length of the cube = x, Original surface area = 6𝑥². New side length = 1.5𝑥, New surface area = 6(1.5𝑥)² = 13.5𝑥². Percentage increase = (New surface area - Original surface area) / Original surface area * 100% = (13.5𝑥² - 6𝑥²) / 6𝑥² * 100% = 125%.','','2026-02-21 01:17:56.077874','2026-02-21 01:17:56.077908',6,1),(3018,'The sides of a square are doubled. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the side = x, original area = x². New side = 2x, new area = (2x)² = 4x². Percentage increase = (4x² - x²) / x² × 100 = 300%.','','2026-02-21 01:17:56.217533','2026-02-21 01:17:56.217568',6,1),(3019,'The radius of a circle increases by 20%. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². If radius increases by 20%, new radius = 1.2r. New area = (1.2r)² = 1.44r², meaning a 44% increase.','','2026-02-21 01:17:56.262685','2026-02-21 01:17:56.262721',6,1),(3020,'The height of a cylinder is doubled and the radius is halved. What happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume = πr²h. New volume = π(½r)²(2h) = πr²h. The volume remains unchanged.','','2026-02-21 01:17:56.426789','2026-02-21 01:17:56.426824',6,1),(3021,'The length of a rectangle is increased by 50%, and the width stays the same. What is the percentage increase in area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area = L × W. Increasing length by 50% makes it 1.5L, so new area = 1.5LW. Increase = 50%.','','2026-02-21 01:17:56.513748','2026-02-21 01:17:56.513780',6,1),(3022,'A cube’s edge length is tripled. By what factor does its volume increase?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. If side is tripled, volume increases by 3³ = 27 times.','','2026-02-21 01:17:56.579515','2026-02-21 01:17:56.579551',6,1),(3023,'All dimensions of a rectangular prism are reduced by 50%. What is the percentage decrease in its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ length × width × height. If each is halved, new volume = (0.5)³ = 0.125, meaning 12.5% remains, so an 87.5% decrease.','','2026-02-21 01:17:56.640867','2026-02-21 01:17:56.640900',6,1),(3024,'The diameter of a circle is reduced by 40%. What is the percentage decrease in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². New radius = 0.6r, new area = 0.36r² → area decreases by 64%.','','2026-02-21 01:17:56.686742','2026-02-21 01:17:56.686775',6,1),(3025,'The volume of a cube doubles. What is the percentage increase in the cube’s side length?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = ³√2 × old side ≈ 1.26×, which is a 26% increase.','','2026-02-21 01:17:56.731658','2026-02-21 01:17:56.731694',6,1),(3026,'A rectangle’s perimeter is 60 cm. If both its length and width increase by 25%, what is the new perimeter?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Perimeter ∝ (L + W). If both increase by 25%, total perimeter increases by 25% → 60 × 1.25 = 75 cm.','','2026-02-21 01:17:56.774808','2026-02-21 01:17:56.774842',6,1),(3027,'The surface area of a cube is 150 cm². If the edge length doubles, what is the new surface area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Surface area ∝ side². Doubling the side makes the area 4 times larger → 150 × 4 = 600 cm².','','2026-02-21 01:17:56.818318','2026-02-21 01:17:56.818394',6,1),(3028,'A cube-shaped gift box has a side length of 10 cm. If the side is increased by 20%, what is the new volume of the box compared to the old one?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = 1.2× old side, so new volume = (1.2)³ = 1.728× the original.','','2026-02-21 01:17:56.878223','2026-02-21 01:17:56.878269',6,1),(3029,'A rectangular water tank is 2 m long, 1.5 m wide, and 1 m high. If the height is doubled, how much more water can it hold?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles the capacity → 2× the amount of water.','','2026-02-21 01:17:56.928483','2026-02-21 01:17:56.928519',6,1),(3030,'A cylindrical candle has a radius of 5 cm and height of 10 cm. If the radius is doubled and height stays the same, how many times greater is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cylinder = πr²h. Doubling radius makes r² → (2r)² = 4r² → volume increases 4 times.','','2026-02-21 01:17:56.978993','2026-02-21 01:17:56.979028',6,1),(3031,'A cone has a radius of 3 cm and height of 8 cm. If both radius and height are doubled, how many times greater is the volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h. If both r and h double → (2r)²(2h) = 8× bigger.','','2026-02-21 01:17:57.035483','2026-02-21 01:17:57.035533',6,1),(3032,'A cylindrical water bottle has a volume of 500 mL. If its height is doubled but the radius stays the same, what will the new volume be?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles volume → 500 mL × 2 = 1 L.','','2026-02-21 01:17:57.091170','2026-02-21 01:17:57.091205',6,1),(3033,'A metal cube is melted and reshaped into a cylinder with the same volume. If the cube’s side is 6 cm, what is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cube = side³ = 6³ = 216 cm³.','','2026-02-21 01:17:57.137262','2026-02-21 01:17:57.137296',6,1),(3034,'A cone and a cylinder have the same base radius and height. How does the volume of the cone compare to the cylinder?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h, while cylinder = πr²h. Therefore, cone = one-third of the cylinder.','','2026-02-21 01:17:57.185953','2026-02-21 01:17:57.185985',6,1),(3035,'A cylindrical jar has a radius of 4 cm and height of 12 cm. If both radius and height increase by 25%, how many times larger is the new volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. New radius = 1.25r, new height = 1.25h → new volume = (1.25)³ = 1.953× larger.','','2026-02-21 01:17:57.237501','2026-02-21 01:17:57.237534',6,1),(3036,'A swimming pool is shaped like a rectangular prism 8 m long, 4 m wide, and 2 m deep. If it is filled halfway, how much water is inside?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Full volume = 8×4×2 = 64 m³. Half full = 64 ÷ 2 = 32 m³.','','2026-02-21 01:17:57.305090','2026-02-21 01:17:57.305122',6,1),(3037,'A cone-shaped paper cup has a height of 9 cm and radius of 3 cm. If both dimensions are halved, what happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. If r and h are halved → (½)³ = ⅛ → volume becomes one-eighth.','','2026-02-21 01:17:57.366771','2026-02-21 01:17:57.366804',6,1),(3038,'What is the HCF of 48 and 72?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Common factors of 48 and 72 include 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 8, 12, 24. The highest is 24.','','2026-02-21 01:18:00.688838','2026-02-21 01:18:00.688875',7,21),(3039,'Factorise: 4x + 8','multiple_choice',1,1,'The common factor of 4x and 8 is 4.','','2026-02-21 01:18:00.775298','2026-02-21 01:18:00.775333',7,21),(3040,'Factorise: 5x + 10','multiple_choice',1,1,'Both terms share a common factor of 5.','','2026-02-21 01:18:00.903308','2026-02-21 01:18:00.903371',7,21),(3041,'Factorise: 3x + 6','multiple_choice',1,1,'The highest common factor of 3x and 6 is 3.','','2026-02-21 01:18:01.053665','2026-02-21 01:18:01.053723',7,21),(3042,'