',1,1,'Both terms share a common factor of 3.','','2026-02-21 01:18:01.853260','2026-02-21 01:18:01.853293',7,21),(3055,'Factorise: 15x - 20','multiple_choice',1,1,'The highest common factor of 15x and 20 is 5.','','2026-02-21 01:18:01.894094','2026-02-21 01:18:01.894148',7,21),(3056,'Factorise: 9x + 12','multiple_choice',1,1,'The highest common factor of 9x and 12 is 3.','','2026-02-21 01:18:01.936706','2026-02-21 01:18:01.936759',7,21),(3057,'Factorise: 8xy + 12x','multiple_choice',1,1,'Common factors are 4 and x.','','2026-02-21 01:18:01.977151','2026-02-21 01:18:01.977203',7,21),(3058,'Factorise: 10ab + 15a','multiple_choice',1,1,'Common factors are 5 and a.','','2026-02-21 01:18:02.021996','2026-02-21 01:18:02.022051',7,21),(3059,'Factorise: 14x + 21y','multiple_choice',1,1,'The highest common factor of 14 and 21 is 7.','','2026-02-21 01:18:02.060865','2026-02-21 01:18:02.060917',7,21),(3060,'Factorise: 18x - 24y','multiple_choice',1,1,'The highest common factor of 18 and 24 is 6.','','2026-02-21 01:18:02.102133','2026-02-21 01:18:02.102187',7,21),(3061,'Factorise: 21xy + 28x','multiple_choice',1,1,'Common factors are 7 and x.','','2026-02-21 01:18:02.140557','2026-02-21 01:18:02.140590',7,21),(3062,'Find the value of X in these right-angled triangles, correct to two decimal places (cos(38°) = 0.7880)','multiple_choice',1,1,'cos(38°) = adjacent/hypotenuse = X/14 ≈ 11.03 m.','questions/year8/trigonometry/image1.png','2026-02-21 01:18:02.305801','2026-02-21 01:18:02.311273',8,24),(3063,'Find the value of X in these right-angled triangles, correct to two decimal places (tan(38°) = 2.6051)','multiple_choice',1,1,'Using tan(38°) = opposite/adjacent: opposite = 25 × tan(38°) ≈ 25 × 2.6051 ≈ 61.88 m.','questions/year8/trigonometry/image2.png','2026-02-21 01:18:02.350464','2026-02-21 01:18:02.357272',8,24),(3064,'Calculate the area of this shape.','multiple_choice',1,1,'Calculate the area using πr².','questions/year6/measurements/image9.png','2026-02-27 21:13:38.565072','2026-02-27 21:13:38.569771',6,1),(3065,'The width of a cube increases by 50%, but it remains a cube. What is the percentage increase in the surface area of the cube?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the original side length of the cube = x, Original surface area = 6𝑥². New side length = 1.5𝑥, New surface area = 6(1.5𝑥)² = 13.5𝑥². Percentage increase = (New surface area - Original surface area) / Original surface area * 100% = (13.5𝑥² - 6𝑥²) / 6𝑥² * 100% = 125%.','','2026-02-27 21:13:38.778449','2026-02-27 21:13:38.778486',6,1),(3066,'The sides of a square are doubled. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Let the side = x, original area = x². New side = 2x, new area = (2x)² = 4x². Percentage increase = (4x² - x²) / x² × 100 = 300%.','','2026-02-27 21:13:38.810887','2026-02-27 21:13:38.810926',6,1),(3067,'The radius of a circle increases by 20%. What is the percentage increase in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². If radius increases by 20%, new radius = 1.2r. New area = (1.2r)² = 1.44r², meaning a 44% increase.','','2026-02-27 21:13:38.845192','2026-02-27 21:13:38.845230',6,1),(3068,'The height of a cylinder is doubled and the radius is halved. What happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume = πr²h. New volume = π(½r)²(2h) = πr²h. The volume remains unchanged.','','2026-02-27 21:13:38.879412','2026-02-27 21:13:38.879449',6,1),(3069,'The length of a rectangle is increased by 50%, and the width stays the same. What is the percentage increase in area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area = L × W. Increasing length by 50% makes it 1.5L, so new area = 1.5LW. Increase = 50%.','','2026-02-27 21:13:38.913542','2026-02-27 21:13:38.913579',6,1),(3070,'A cube’s edge length is tripled. By what factor does its volume increase?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. If side is tripled, volume increases by 3³ = 27 times.','','2026-02-27 21:13:38.946904','2026-02-27 21:13:38.946940',6,1),(3071,'All dimensions of a rectangular prism are reduced by 50%. What is the percentage decrease in its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ length × width × height. If each is halved, new volume = (0.5)³ = 0.125, meaning 12.5% remains, so an 87.5% decrease.','','2026-02-27 21:13:38.981858','2026-02-27 21:13:38.981898',6,1),(3072,'The diameter of a circle is reduced by 40%. What is the percentage decrease in its area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Area ∝ r². New radius = 0.6r, new area = 0.36r² → area decreases by 64%.','','2026-02-27 21:13:39.015744','2026-02-27 21:13:39.015782',6,1),(3073,'The volume of a cube doubles. What is the percentage increase in the cube’s side length?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = ³√2 × old side ≈ 1.26×, which is a 26% increase.','','2026-02-27 21:13:39.049310','2026-02-27 21:13:39.049360',6,1),(3074,'A rectangle’s perimeter is 60 cm. If both its length and width increase by 25%, what is the new perimeter?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Perimeter ∝ (L + W). If both increase by 25%, total perimeter increases by 25% → 60 × 1.25 = 75 cm.','','2026-02-27 21:13:39.085762','2026-02-27 21:13:39.085801',6,1),(3075,'The surface area of a cube is 150 cm². If the edge length doubles, what is the new surface area?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Surface area ∝ side². Doubling the side makes the area 4 times larger → 150 × 4 = 600 cm².','','2026-02-27 21:13:39.120054','2026-02-27 21:13:39.120092',6,1),(3076,'A cube-shaped gift box has a side length of 10 cm. If the side is increased by 20%, what is the new volume of the box compared to the old one?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ side³. New side = 1.2× old side, so new volume = (1.2)³ = 1.728× the original.','','2026-02-27 21:13:39.157502','2026-02-27 21:13:39.157539',6,1),(3077,'A rectangular water tank is 2 m long, 1.5 m wide, and 1 m high. If the height is doubled, how much more water can it hold?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles the capacity → 2× the amount of water.','','2026-02-27 21:13:39.194336','2026-02-27 21:13:39.194372',6,1),(3078,'A cylindrical candle has a radius of 5 cm and height of 10 cm. If the radius is doubled and height stays the same, how many times greater is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cylinder = πr²h. Doubling radius makes r² → (2r)² = 4r² → volume increases 4 times.','','2026-02-27 21:13:39.240362','2026-02-27 21:13:39.240412',6,1),(3079,'A cone has a radius of 3 cm and height of 8 cm. If both radius and height are doubled, how many times greater is the volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h. If both r and h double → (2r)²(2h) = 8× bigger.','','2026-02-27 21:13:39.278778','2026-02-27 21:13:39.278816',6,1),(3080,'A cylindrical water bottle has a volume of 500 mL. If its height is doubled but the radius stays the same, what will the new volume be?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ height. Doubling height doubles volume → 500 mL × 2 = 1 L.','','2026-02-27 21:13:39.347986','2026-02-27 21:13:39.348050',6,1),(3081,'A metal cube is melted and reshaped into a cylinder with the same volume. If the cube’s side is 6 cm, what is its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cube = side³ = 6³ = 216 cm³.','','2026-02-27 21:13:39.391539','2026-02-27 21:13:39.391598',6,1),(3082,'A cone and a cylinder have the same base radius and height. How does the volume of the cone compare to the cylinder?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume of a cone = ⅓πr²h, while cylinder = πr²h. Therefore, cone = one-third of the cylinder.','','2026-02-27 21:13:39.427995','2026-02-27 21:13:39.428036',6,1),(3083,'A cylindrical jar has a radius of 4 cm and height of 12 cm. If both radius and height increase by 25%, how many times larger is the new volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. New radius = 1.25r, new height = 1.25h → new volume = (1.25)³ = 1.953× larger.','','2026-02-27 21:13:39.463941','2026-02-27 21:13:39.464017',6,1),(3084,'A swimming pool is shaped like a rectangular prism 8 m long, 4 m wide, and 2 m deep. If it is filled halfway, how much water is inside?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Full volume = 8×4×2 = 64 m³. Half full = 64 ÷ 2 = 32 m³.','','2026-02-27 21:13:39.500524','2026-02-27 21:13:39.500561',6,1),(3085,'A cone-shaped paper cup has a height of 9 cm and radius of 3 cm. If both dimensions are halved, what happens to its volume?','multiple_choice',1,1,'Volume ∝ r²h. If r and h are halved → (½)³ = ⅛ → volume becomes one-eighth.','','2026-02-27 21:13:39.533626','2026-02-27 21:13:39.533664',6,1),(3086,'Calculate: 6/12 + 7/12','multiple_choice',1,1,'The denominators are the same, so add the numerators: 6 + 7 = 13.','','2026-02-27 21:13:42.672133','2026-02-27 21:13:42.672168',7,15),(3087,'Calculate: 5/8 - 1/4','multiple_choice',1,1,'Convert 1/4 to 2/8, then subtract: 5/8 − 2/8 = 3/8.','','2026-02-27 21:13:42.704305','2026-02-27 21:13:42.704342',7,15),(3088,'Calculate: 11/12 - 2/3','multiple_choice',1,1,'Convert 2/3 to 8/12, then subtract: 11/12 − 8/12 = 3/12 = 1/4.','','2026-02-27 21:13:42.732717','2026-02-27 21:13:42.732755',7,15),(3089,'Calculate: 2 3/5 + 3/10','multiple_choice',1,1,'Convert 3/5 to 6/10, then add: 6/10 + 3/10 = 9/10. Final answer is 2 9/10.','','2026-02-27 21:13:42.766172','2026-02-27 21:13:42.766210',7,15),(3090,'Calculate: 3/4 + 5/8','multiple_choice',1,1,'Convert 3/4 to 6/8, then add: 6/8 + 5/8 = 11/8.','','2026-02-27 21:13:42.797824','2026-02-27 21:13:42.797862',7,15),(3091,'Calculate: 7/9 - 1/3','multiple_choice',1,1,'Convert 1/3 to 3/9, then subtract: 7/9 − 3/9 = 4/9.','','2026-02-27 21:13:42.828525','2026-02-27 21:13:42.828563',7,15),(3092,'Calculate: 5/6 + 1/3','multiple_choice',1,1,'Convert 1/3 to 2/6, then add: 5/6 + 2/6 = 7/6.','','2026-02-27 21:13:42.864483','2026-02-27 21:13:42.864521',7,15),(3093,'Calculate: 9/10 - 3/5','multiple_choice',1,1,'Convert 3/5 to 6/10, then subtract: 9/10 − 6/10 = 3/10.','','2026-02-27 21:13:42.902628','2026-02-27 21:13:42.902664',7,15),(3094,'Calculate: 1 1/2 + 3/4','multiple_choice',1,1,'Convert 1/2 to 2/4, then add: 2/4 + 3/4 = 5/4 = 1 1/4. Total = 2 1/4.','','2026-02-27 21:13:43.020707','2026-02-27 21:13:43.020747',7,15),(3095,'Calculate: 4/5 - 2/10','multiple_choice',1,1,'Convert 4/5 to 8/10, then subtract: 8/10 − 2/10 = 6/10 = 3/5.','','2026-02-27 21:13:43.054208','2026-02-27 21:13:43.054242',7,15),(3096,'Calculate: 2 1/4 + 1/2','multiple_choice',1,1,'Convert 1/2 to 2/4, then add: 1/4 + 2/4 = 3/4.','','2026-02-27 21:13:43.100498','2026-02-27 21:13:43.100538',7,15),(3097,'Calculate: 13/15 - 4/5','multiple_choice',1,1,'Convert 4/5 to 12/15, then subtract: 13/15 − 12/15 = 1/15.','','2026-02-27 21:13:43.139898','2026-02-27 21:13:43.139936',7,15),(3098,'Write 3/5 and 2/4 as equivalent fractions with a common denominator.','multiple_choice',1,1,'The lowest common denominator of 5 and 4 is 20. Convert 3/5 = 12/20 and 2/4 = 10/20.','','2026-02-27 21:13:43.215031','2026-02-27 21:13:43.215070',7,15),(3099,'Write 5/8 and 3/4 as equivalent fractions with a common denominator.','multiple_choice',1,1,'The lowest common denominator of 8 and 4 is 8. Convert 3/4 = 6/8.','','2026-02-27 21:13:43.308499','2026-02-27 21:13:43.308536',7,15),(3100,'Write 2/10 and 1/15 as equivalent fractions with a common denominator.','multiple_choice',1,1,'The lowest common denominator of 10 and 15 is 30. Convert 2/10 = 6/30 and 1/15 = 2/30.','','2026-02-27 21:13:43.431683','2026-02-27 21:13:43.431720',7,15),(3101,'Write 2/3 and 1/8 as equivalent fractions with a common denominator.','multiple_choice',1,1,'The lowest common denominator of 3 and 8 is 24. Convert 2/3 = 16/24 and 1/8 = 3/24.','','2026-02-27 21:13:43.543374','2026-02-27 21:13:43.543433',7,15),(3102,'Compare: 3/7 and 2/3','multiple_choice',1,1,'Convert to a common denominator: 3/7 = 9/21, 2/3 = 14/21. Since 9/21 < 14/21, 3/7 < 2/3.','','2026-02-27 21:13:43.582362','2026-02-27 21:13:43.582398',7,15),(3103,'Compare: 2/5 and 1/2','multiple_choice',1,1,'Common denominator: 2/5 = 4/10, 1/2 = 5/10. Since 4/10 < 5/10, 2/5 < 1/2.','','2026-02-27 21:13:43.612946','2026-02-27 21:13:43.6